Name: Bulbasaur
Pokedex Entry: For some time after its birth it uses the nutrients that are packed into the seed on its back in order to grow.

Name: Ivysaur
Pokedex Entry: The more sunlight Ivysaur bathes in the more strength wells up within it allowing the bud on its back to grow larger.

Name: Venusaur
Pokedex Entry: While it basks in the sun it can convert the light into energy. As a result it is more powerful in the summertime.

Name: Charmander
Pokedex Entry: The flame on its tail shows the strength of its life-force. If Charmander is weak the flame also burns weakly.

Name: Charmeleon
Pokedex Entry: When it swings its burning tail the temperature around it rises higher and higher tormenting its opponents.

Name: Charizard
Pokedex Entry: If Charizard becomes truly angered the flame at the tip of its tail burns in a light blue shade.

Name: Squirtle
Pokedex Entry: After birth its back swells and hardens into a shell. It sprays a potent foam from its mouth.

Name: Wartortle
Pokedex Entry: Wartortle’s long furry tail is a symbol of longevity so this Pokemon is quite popular among older people.

Name: Blastoise
Pokedex Entry: It deliberately increases its body weight so it can withstand the recoil of the water jets it fires.

Name: Caterpie
Pokedex Entry: For protection it releases a horrible stench from the antenna on its head to drive away enemies.

Name: Metapod
Pokedex Entry: It is waiting for the moment to evolve. At this stage it can only harden so it remains motionless to avoid attack.

Name: Butterfree
Pokedex Entry: It loves the nectar of flowers and can locate flower patches that have even tiny amounts of pollen.

Name: Weedle
Pokedex Entry: Beware of the sharp stinger on its head. It hides in grass and bushes where it eats leaves.

Name: Kakuna
Pokedex Entry: Able to move only slightly. When endangered it may stick out its stinger and poison its enemy.

Name: Beedrill
Pokedex Entry: It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.

Name: Pidgey
Pokedex Entry: Very docile. If attacked it will often kick up sand to protect itself rather than fight back.

Name: Pidgeotto
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is full of vitality. It constantly flies around its large territory in search of prey.

Name: Pidgeot
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon flies at Mach 2 speed seeking prey. Its large talons are feared as wicked weapons.

Name: Rattata
Pokedex Entry: Will chew on anything with its fangs. If you see one you can be certain that 40 more live in the area.

Name: Raticate
Pokedex Entry: Its hind feet are webbed. They act as flippers so it can swim in rivers and hunt for prey.

Name: Spearow
Pokedex Entry: Inept at flying high. However it can fly around very fast to protect its territory.

Name: Fearow
Pokedex Entry: A Pokemon that dates back many years. If it senses danger it flies high and away instantly.

Name: Ekans
Pokedex Entry: It can freely detach its jaw to swallow large prey whole. It can become too heavy to move however.

Name: Arbok
Pokedex Entry: The pattern on its belly appears to be a frightening face. Weak foes will flee just at the sight of the pattern.

Name: Pikachu
Pokedex Entry: When it is angered it immediately discharges the energy stored in the pouches in its cheeks.

Name: Raichu
Pokedex Entry: Its tail discharges electricity into the ground protecting it from getting shocked.

Name: Sandshrew
Pokedex Entry: It digs deep burrows to live in. When in danger it rolls up its body to withstand attacks.

Name: Sandslash
Pokedex Entry: It is adept at attacking with the spines on its back and its sharp claws while quickly scurrying about.

Name: Nidoran
Pokedex Entry: Females are more sensitive to smells than males. While foraging they’ll use their whiskers to check wind direction and stay downwind of predators.

Name: Nidorina
Pokedex Entry: The horn on its head has atrophied. It’s thought that this happens so Nidorina’s children won’t get poked while their mother is feeding them.

Name: Nidoqueen
Pokedex Entry: Nidoqueen is better at defense than offense. With scales like armor this Pokemon will shield its children from any kind of attack.

Name: Nidoran
Pokedex Entry: The horn on a male Nidoran’s forehead contains a powerful poison. This is a very cautious Pokemon always straining its large ears.

Name: Nidorino
Pokedex Entry: With a horn that’s harder than diamond this Pokemon goes around shattering boulders as it searches for a moon stone.

Name: Nidoking
Pokedex Entry: When it goes on a rampage it’s impossible to control. But in the presence of a Nidoqueen it’s lived with for a long time Nidoking calms down.

Name: Clefairy
Pokedex Entry: On nights with a full moon Clefairy gather from all over and dance. Bathing in moonlight makes them float.

Name: Clefable
Pokedex Entry: Said to live in quiet remote mountains this type of fairy has a strong aversion to being seen.

Name: Vulpix
Pokedex Entry: If it is attacked by an enemy that is stronger than itself it feigns injury to fool the enemy and escapes.

Name: Ninetales
Pokedex Entry: Some legends claim that each of its nine tails has its own unique type of special mystical power.

Name: Jigglypuff
Pokedex Entry: When its huge eyes waver it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.

Name: Wigglytuff
Pokedex Entry: It has a very fine fur. Take care not to make it angry or it may inflate steadily and hit with a body slam.

Name: Zubat
Pokedex Entry: It emits ultrasonic waves from its mouth to check its surroundings. Even in tight caves Zubat flies around with skill.

Name: Golbat
Pokedex Entry: It loves to drink other creatures’ blood. It’s said that if it finds others of its kind going hungry it sometimes shares the blood it’s gathered.

Name: Oddish
Pokedex Entry: Its scientific name is Oddium wanderus. It is said to cover distances as far as 1000 feet when night falls walking on its two roots.

Name: Gloom
Pokedex Entry: The fluid that oozes from its mouth isn’t drool. It is a nectar that is used to attract prey.

Name: Vileplume
Pokedex Entry: The bud bursts into bloom with a bang. It then starts scattering allergenic poisonous pollen.

Name: Paras
Pokedex Entry: Burrows under the ground to gnaw on tree roots. The mushrooms on its back absorb most of the nutrition.

Name: Parasect
Pokedex Entry: The bug host is drained of energy by the mushroom on its back. The mushroom appears to do all the thinking.

Name: Venonat
Pokedex Entry: Poison oozes from all over its body. It catches small bug Pokemon at night that are attracted by light.

Name: Venomoth
Pokedex Entry: The wings are covered with dustlike scales. Every time it flaps its wings it looses highly toxic dust.

Name: Diglett
Pokedex Entry: It lives about one yard underground where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears aboveground.

Name: Dugtrio
Pokedex Entry: Its three heads bob separately up and down to loosen the soil nearby making it easier for it to burrow.

Name: Meowth
Pokedex Entry: All it does is sleep during the daytime. At night it patrols its territory with its eyes aglow.

Name: Persian
Pokedex Entry: Although its fur has many admirers it is tough to raise as a pet because of its fickle meanness.

Name: Psyduck
Pokedex Entry: It is constantly wracked by a headache. When the headache turns intense it begins using mysterious powers.

Name: Golduck
Pokedex Entry: When it swims at full speed using its long webbed limbs its forehead somehow begins to glow.

Name: Mankey
Pokedex Entry: It lives in groups in the treetops. If it loses sight of its group it becomes infuriated by its loneliness.

Name: Primeape
Pokedex Entry: It becomes wildly furious if it even senses someone looking at it. It chases anyone that meets its glare.

Name: Growlithe
Pokedex Entry: It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.

Name: Arcanine
Pokedex Entry: An ancient picture scroll shows that people were captivated by its movement as it ran through prairies.

Name: Poliwag
Pokedex Entry: The swirl on its belly is its insides showing through the skin. It appears more clearly after Poliwag eats.

Name: Poliwhirl
Pokedex Entry: Its two legs are well developed. Even though it can live on the ground it prefers living in water.

Name: Poliwrath
Pokedex Entry: Although it’s skilled in a style of dynamic swimming that uses all its muscles for some reason it lives on dry land.

Name: Abra
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon uses its psychic powers while it sleeps. The contents of Abra’s dreams affect the powers that the Pokemon wields.

Name: Kadabra
Pokedex Entry: Using its psychic power Kadabra levitates as it sleeps. It uses its springy tail as a pillow.

Name: Alakazam
Pokedex Entry: It has an incredibly high level of intelligence. Some say that Alakazam remembers everything that ever happens to it from birth till death.

Name: Machop
Pokedex Entry: Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it’s the size of a human child it can hurl 100 grown-ups.

Name: Machoke
Pokedex Entry: Its muscular body is so powerful it must wear a power-save belt to be able to regulate its motions.

Name: Machamp
Pokedex Entry: It punches with its four arms at blinding speed. It can launch 1000 punches in two seconds.

Name: Bellsprout
Pokedex Entry: No matter what Bellsprout is doing if it detects movement nearby it will immediately react by reaching out with its thin vines.

Name: Weepinbell
Pokedex Entry: Even though it is filled with acid it does not melt because it also oozes a protective fluid.

Name: Victreebel
Pokedex Entry: It lures prey into its mouth with a nectar-like aroma. The helpless prey is melted with a dissolving fluid.

Name: Tentacool
Pokedex Entry: When the tide goes out dehydrated Tentacool can be found left behind on the shore.

Name: Tentacruel
Pokedex Entry: On the rare occasions that large outbreaks of Tentacruel occur all fish Pokemon disappear from the surrounding sea.

Name: Geodude
Pokedex Entry: At rest it looks just like a rock. Carelessly stepping on it will make it swing its fists angrily.

Name: Graveler
Pokedex Entry: A slow walker it rolls to move. It pays no attention to any object that happens to be in its path.

Name: Golem
Pokedex Entry: It is enclosed in a hard shell that is as rugged as slabs of rock. It sheds skin once a year to grow larger.

Name: Ponyta
Pokedex Entry: About an hour after birth Ponyta’s fiery mane and tail grow out giving the Pokemon an impressive appearance.

Name: Rapidash
Pokedex Entry: It gallops at nearly 150 mph. With its mane blazing ferociously it races as if it were an arrow.

Name: Slowpoke
Pokedex Entry: It is incredibly slow and dopey. It takes five seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.

Name: Slowbro
Pokedex Entry: When a Slowpoke went hunting in the sea its tail was bitten by a Shellder. That made it evolve into Slowbro.

Name: Magnemite
Pokedex Entry: The electromagnetic waves emitted by the units at the sides of its head expel antigravity which allows it to float.

Name: Magneton
Pokedex Entry: Three Magnemite are linked by a strong magnetic force. Earaches will occur if you get too close.

Name: Farfetch'd
Pokedex Entry: It can’t live without the stalk it holds. That’s why it defends the stalk from attackers with its life.

Name: Doduo
Pokedex Entry: Its twin heads have exactly the same genes and battle in perfect sync with each other.

Name: Dodrio
Pokedex Entry: It now has three hearts and three sets of lungs. Though it can’t run as fast as Doduo Dodrio can keep running for longer stretches of time.

Name: Seel
Pokedex Entry: The protrusion on its head is very hard. It is used for bashing through thick ice.

Name: Dewgong
Pokedex Entry: It sleeps under shallow ocean waters during the day then looks for food at night when it’s colder.

Name: Grimer
Pokedex Entry: Born from sludge these Pokemon now gather in polluted places and increase the bacteria in their bodies.

Name: Muk
Pokedex Entry: It’s thickly covered with a filthy vile sludge. It is so toxic even its footprints contain poison.

Name: Shellder
Pokedex Entry: It is encased in a shell that is harder than diamond. Inside however it is surprisingly tender.

Name: Cloyster
Pokedex Entry: Cloyster that live in seas with harsh tidal currents grow large sharp spikes on their shells.

Name: Gastly
Pokedex Entry: It wraps its opponent in its gas-like body slowly weakening its prey by poisoning it through the skin.

Name: Haunter
Pokedex Entry: It likes to lurk in the dark and tap shoulders with a gaseous hand. Its touch causes endless shuddering.

Name: Gengar
Pokedex Entry: To steal the life of its target it slips into the prey’s shadow and silently waits for an opportunity.

Name: Onix
Pokedex Entry: As it digs through the ground it absorbs many hard objects. This is what makes its body so solid.

Name: Drowzee
Pokedex Entry: It remembers every dream it eats. It rarely eats the dreams of adults because children’s are much tastier.

Name: Hypno
Pokedex Entry: When it locks eyes with an enemy it will use a mix of psi moves such as Hypnosis and Confusion.

Name: Krabby
Pokedex Entry: It can be found near the sea. The large pincers grow back if they are torn out of their sockets.

Name: Kingler
Pokedex Entry: The larger pincer has 10000-horsepower strength. However it is so heavy it is difficult to aim.

Name: Voltorb
Pokedex Entry: It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven a sudden jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.

Name: Electrode
Pokedex Entry: The more energy it charges up the faster it gets. But this also makes it more likely to explode.

Name: Exeggcute
Pokedex Entry: If you touch one of Exeggcute’s heads mistaking it for an egg the other heads will quickly gather and attack you in a swarm.

Name: Exeggutor
Pokedex Entry: It is called the Walking Jungle. Each of the nuts has a face and a will of its own.

Name: Cubone
Pokedex Entry: When the memory of its departed mother brings it to tears its cries echo mournfully within the skull it wears on its head.

Name: Marowak
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon overcame its sorrow to evolve a sturdy new body. Marowak faces its opponents bravely using a bone as a weapon.

Name: Hitmonlee
Pokedex Entry: At the exact moment it lands a kick on its target Hitmonlee hardens the muscles on the sole of its foot maximizing the power of the kick.

Name: Hitmonchan
Pokedex Entry: It corners its foes with combo punches from both sides then finishes them off with a single straight punch launched at over 300 mph.

Name: Lickitung
Pokedex Entry: If this Pokemon’s sticky saliva gets on you and you don’t clean it off an intense itch will set in. The itch won’t go away either.

Name: Koffing
Pokedex Entry: Toxic gas is held within its thin balloon-shaped body so it can cause massive explosions.

Name: Weezing
Pokedex Entry: Top-grade perfume is made using its internal poison gases by diluting them to the highest level.

Name: Rhyhorn
Pokedex Entry: Rhyhorn claims an area with over a six mile radius as its territory. It apparently forgets where this territory is when running however.

Name: Rhydon
Pokedex Entry: The horn of a Rhydon is powerful enough to crush raw diamonds. These Pokemon polish their horns by bashing them together.

Name: Chansey
Pokedex Entry: This kindly Pokemon lays highly nutritious eggs and shares them with injured Pokemon or people.

Name: Tangela
Pokedex Entry: Hidden beneath a tangle of vines that grows nonstop even if the vines are torn off this Pokemon’s true appearance remains a mystery.

Name: Kangaskhan
Pokedex Entry: Although it’s carrying its baby in a pouch on its belly Kangaskhan is swift on its feet. It intimidates its opponents with quick jabs.

Name: Horsea
Pokedex Entry: If attacked—even by a large enemy—Horsea effortlessly swims to safety by utilizing its well-developed dorsal fin.

Name: Seadra
Pokedex Entry: The male raises the young. If it is approached while caring for young it will use its toxic spines to fend off the intruder.

Name: Goldeen
Pokedex Entry: Its dorsal pectoral and tail fins wave elegantly in water. That is why it is known as the Water Dancer.

Name: Seaking
Pokedex Entry: In autumn its body becomes more fatty in preparing to propose to a mate. It takes on beautiful colors.

Name: Staryu
Pokedex Entry: If you visit a beach at the end of summer you’ll be able to see groups of Staryu lighting up in a steady rhythm.

Name: Starmie
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon has an organ known as its core. The organ glows in seven colors when Starmie is unleashing its potent psychic powers.

Name: Mr. Mime
Pokedex Entry: It is a pantomime expert that can create invisible but solid walls using miming gestures.

Name: Scyther
Pokedex Entry: It slashes through grass with its sharp scythes moving too fast for the human eye to track.

Name: Jynx
Pokedex Entry: In certain parts of Galar Jynx was once feared and worshiped as the Queen of Ice.

Name: Electabuzz
Pokedex Entry: Its body constantly discharges electricity. Getting close to it will make your hair stand on end.

Name: Magmar
Pokedex Entry: Found near the mouth of a volcano. This fire-breather’s body temperature is nearly 2200 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Pinsir
Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon judge one another based on pincers. Thicker more impressive pincers make for more popularity with the opposite gender.

Name: Tauros
Pokedex Entry: When it targets an enemy it charges furiously while whipping its body with its long tails.

Name: Magikarp
Pokedex Entry: An underpowered pathetic Pokemon. It may jump high on rare occasions but never more than seven feet.

Name: Gyarados
Pokedex Entry: Once it appears it goes on a rampage. It remains enraged until it demolishes everything around it.

Name: Lapras
Pokedex Entry: It ferries people across the sea on its back. It may sing an enchanting cry if it is in a good mood.

Name: Ditto
Pokedex Entry: Its transformation ability is perfect. However if made to laugh it can’t maintain its disguise.

Name: Eevee
Pokedex Entry: Its ability to evolve into many forms allows it to adapt smoothly and perfectly to any environment.

Name: Vaporeon
Pokedex Entry: It lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with a fin which is often mistaken for a mermaid’s.

Name: Jolteon
Pokedex Entry: It concentrates the weak electric charges emitted by its cells and launches wicked lightning bolts.

Name: Flareon
Pokedex Entry: Inhaled air is carried to its flame sac heated and exhaled as fire that reaches over 3000 degrees Fahrenheit.

Name: Porygon
Pokedex Entry: It is an artificial Pokemon. Since it doesn’t breathe people are excited by its potential to be useful in any environment.

Name: Omanyte
Pokedex Entry: Because some Omanyte manage to escape after being restored or are released into the wild by people this species is becoming a problem.

Name: Omastar
Pokedex Entry: Weighed down by a large and heavy shell Omastar couldn’t move very fast. Some say it went extinct because it was unable to catch food.

Name: Kabuto
Pokedex Entry: This species is almost entirely extinct. Kabuto molt every three days making their shells harder and harder.

Name: Kabutops
Pokedex Entry: Kabutops slices its prey apart and sucks out the fluids. The discarded body parts become food for other Pokemon.

Name: Aerodactyl
Pokedex Entry: This is a ferocious Pokemon from ancient times. Apparently even modern technology is incapable of producing a perfectly restored specimen.

Name: Snorlax
Pokedex Entry: This gluttonous Pokemon eats constantly apart from when it’s asleep. It devours nearly 900 pounds of food per day.

Name: Articuno
Pokedex Entry: This legendary bird Pokemon can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.

Name: Zapdos
Pokedex Entry: This legendary Pokemon is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.

Name: Moltres
Pokedex Entry: It is one of the legendary bird Pokemon. Its appearance is said to indicate the coming of spring.

Name: Dratini
Pokedex Entry: It sheds many layers of skin as it grows larger. During this process it is protected by a rapid waterfall.

Name: Dragonair
Pokedex Entry: They say that if it emits an aura from its whole body the weather will begin to change instantly.

Name: Dragonite
Pokedex Entry: It is said that somewhere in the ocean lies an island where these gather. Only they live there.

Name: Mewtwo
Pokedex Entry: Its DNA is almost the same as Mew’s. However its size and disposition are vastly different.

Name: Mew
Pokedex Entry: When viewed through a microscope this Pokemon’s short fine delicate hair can be seen.

Name: Chikorita
Pokedex Entry: It loves to bask in the sunlight. It uses the leaf on its head to seek out warm places.

Name: Bayleef
Pokedex Entry: The spicy scent that wafts from around Bayleef’s neck somehow makes those who smell it want to fight.

Name: Meganium
Pokedex Entry: Anyone who stands beside it becomes refreshed just as if they were soaking in the soothing atmosphere of a forest.

Name: Cyndaquil
Pokedex Entry: It usually stays hunched over. If it is angry or surprised it shoots flames out of its back.

Name: Quilava
Pokedex Entry: Before battle it turns its back on its opponent to demonstrate how ferociously its fire blazes.

Name: Typhlosion
Pokedex Entry: It has a secret devastating move. It rubs its blazing fur to cause huge explosions.

Name: Totodile
Pokedex Entry: Its powerful well-developed jaws are capable of crushing anything. Even its Trainer must be careful.

Name: Croconaw
Pokedex Entry: The tips of its fangs are slanted backward. Once those fangs clamp down the prey has no hope of escape.

Name: Feraligatr
Pokedex Entry: When it bites with its massive and powerful jaws it shakes its head and savagely tears its victim up.

Name: Sentret
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is extremely cautious. Its supple tail is well muscled and firm to the touch.

Name: Furret
Pokedex Entry: It raises its offspring inside a long narrow nest. Once they’re old enough it takes them outside the nest to prepare them for independence.

Name: Hoothoot
Pokedex Entry: Hoothoot’s internal clock is precise at all times. It tilts its head in a fixed rhythm.

Name: Noctowl
Pokedex Entry: Its eyes are specially adapted. They concentrate even faint light and enable it to see in the dark.

Name: Ledyba
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is very sensitive to cold. In the warmth of Alola it appears quite lively.

Name: Ledian
Pokedex Entry: It’s said that the patterns on its back are related to the stars in the night sky but the details of that relationship remain unclear.

Name: Spinarak
Pokedex Entry: Even while there are prey ensnared in its nest of spun thread Spinarak will wait motionlessly until darkness falls.

Name: Ariados
Pokedex Entry: A single strand of a special thread is endlessly spun out of its rear. The thread leads back to its nest.

Name: Crobat
Pokedex Entry: Both of its legs have turned into wings. Without a sound Crobat flies swiftly toward its prey and sinks its fangs into the nape of its target’s neck.

Name: Chinchou
Pokedex Entry: It lives in ocean depths beyond the reach of sunlight. It flashes lights on its antennae to communicate with others of its kind.

Name: Lanturn
Pokedex Entry: Portions of its dorsal fin mutated becoming the parts that glow brightly to lure prey.

Name: Pichu
Pokedex Entry: It is unskilled at storing electric power. Any kind of shock causes it to discharge energy spontaneously.

Name: Cleffa
Pokedex Entry: On late nights illuminated by shooting stars it gazes intently skyward as if thinking of its home.

Name: Igglybuff
Pokedex Entry: Its body has a faintly sweet scent and is bouncy and soft. If it bounces even once it cannot stop.

Name: Togepi
Pokedex Entry: The shell seems to be filled with joy. It is said that it will share good luck when treated kindly.

Name: Togetic
Pokedex Entry: They say that it will appear before kindhearted caring people and shower them with happiness.

Name: Natu
Pokedex Entry: It is extremely good at climbing tree trunks and likes to eat the new sprouts on the trees.

Name: Xatu
Pokedex Entry: They say that it stays still and quiet because it is seeing both the past and future at the same time.

Name: Mareep
Pokedex Entry: If static electricity builds in its body its fleece doubles in volume. Touching it will shock you.

Name: Flaaffy
Pokedex Entry: As a result of storing too much electricity it developed patches where even downy wool won’t grow.

Name: Ampharos
Pokedex Entry: The bright light on its tail can be seen far away. It has been treasured since ancient times as a beacon.

Name: Bellossom
Pokedex Entry: Due to the effects of the Sun Stone it is now active during the daytime. It likes to dance in pools of sunlight.

Name: Marill
Pokedex Entry: The fur on its body naturally repels water. It can stay dry even when it plays in the water.

Name: Azumarill
Pokedex Entry: Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of things in water and tell what they are.

Name: Sudowoodo
Pokedex Entry: Although it always pretends to be a tree its composition appears more similar to rock than to vegetation.

Name: Politoed
Pokedex Entry: If Poliwag and Poliwhirl hear its echoing cry they respond by gathering from far and wide.

Name: Hoppip
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is blown across vast distances by the wind. It is unclear where the Hoppip of Paldea originally came from.

Name: Skiploom
Pokedex Entry: Skiploom enthusiasts can apparently tell where a Skiploom was born by the scent drifting from the flower on the Pokemon’s head.

Name: Jumpluff
Pokedex Entry: Jumpluff travels on seasonal winds. Once its cotton spores run out its journey ends as does its life.

Name: Aipom
Pokedex Entry: It lives atop tall trees. When leaping from branch to branch it deftly uses its tail for balance.

Name: Sunkern
Pokedex Entry: It suddenly falls out of the sky in the morning. Knowing it’s weak it simply feeds until it evolves.

Name: Sunflora
Pokedex Entry: In the daytime it rushes about in a hectic manner but it comes to a complete stop when the sun sets.

Name: Yanma
Pokedex Entry: As Yanma surveys its territory it periodically stops to hover in place by flapping its wings at high speeds.

Name: Wooper
Pokedex Entry: A transparent mucous membrane covers its body. Touching it bare-handed will cause a tingling numbness.

Name: Quagsire
Pokedex Entry: This carefree Pokemon has an easygoing nature. While swimming it always bumps into boat hulls.

Name: Espeon
Pokedex Entry: The tip of its forked tail quivers when it is predicting its opponent’s next move.

Name: Umbreon
Pokedex Entry: When exposed to the moon’s aura the rings on its body glow faintly and it gains a mysterious power.

Name: Murkrow
Pokedex Entry: Feared and loathed by many it is believed to bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.

Name: Slowking
Pokedex Entry: When its head was bitten toxins entered Slowpoke’s head and unlocked an extraordinary power.

Name: Misdreavus
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon startles people in the middle of the night. It gathers fear as its energy.

Name: Unown
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is shaped like ancient writing. It is a mystery as to which came first the ancient writings or the various Unown. Research into this topic is ongoing but nothing is known.

Name: Wobbuffet
Pokedex Entry: It hates light and shock. If attacked it inflates its body to pump up its counterstrike.

Name: Girafarig
Pokedex Entry: Though very small the brain in its tail is still considered an important organ because it emits powerful psychic energy.

Name: Pineco
Pokedex Entry: It likes to make its shell thicker by adding layers of tree bark. The additional weight doesn’t bother it.

Name: Forretress
Pokedex Entry: It’s usually found hanging on to a fat tree trunk. It shoots out bits of its shell when it sees action.

Name: Dunsparce
Pokedex Entry: It creates mazes in dark locations. When spotted it flees into the ground by digging with its tail.

Name: Gligar
Pokedex Entry: It builds its nest on a steep cliff. When it is done gliding it hops along the ground back to its nest.

Name: Steelix
Pokedex Entry: It is said that if an Onix lives for over 100 years its composition changes to become diamond-like.

Name: Snubbull
Pokedex Entry: In truth it is a cowardly Pokemon. It growls eagerly in order to hide its fear from its opponent.

Name: Granbull
Pokedex Entry: It is actually timid and easily spooked. If attacked it desperately flails its limbs about in an attempt to repel its opponent.

Name: Qwilfish
Pokedex Entry: Be cautious if this Pokemon starts sucking in water—it will soon attack by scattering the toxic spikes that grow all over its body.

Name: Scizor
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon’s pincers which contain steel can crush any hard object they get ahold of into bits.

Name: Shuckle
Pokedex Entry: It stores berries inside its shell. To avoid attacks it hides beneath rocks and remains completely still.

Name: Heracross
Pokedex Entry: It loves sweet nectar. To keep all the nectar to itself it hurls rivals away with its prized horn.

Name: Sneasel
Pokedex Entry: This cunning Pokemon hides under the cover of darkness waiting to attack its prey.

Name: Teddiursa
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon discreetly follows Combee to find their hive. It scoops up big dollops of honey in its palms to eat.

Name: Ursaring
Pokedex Entry: It usually wears a hardened expression but when it’s licking up honey—which it loves—the joy it feels will cause it to break into a wide grin.

Name: Slugma
Pokedex Entry: Its lava body can cool and chip away at times but a magma bath will heal it right up.

Name: Magcargo
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon lives near the craters of volcanoes. It stores fire energy in its shell of cooled and hardened magma.

Name: Swinub
Pokedex Entry: It searches for food by digging into the ground with its snout. Even frozen ground doesn’t give it any trouble.

Name: Piloswine
Pokedex Entry: Covered by a shaggy coat it is resistant to the cold. Its tusks of ice thicken when it snows.

Name: Corsola
Pokedex Entry: Many live in the clean seas of the south. They apparently can’t live in polluted waters.

Name: Remoraid
Pokedex Entry: The water they shoot from their mouths can hit moving prey from more than 300 feet away.

Name: Octillery
Pokedex Entry: It has a tendency to want to be in holes. It prefers rock crags or pots and sprays ink from them before attacking.

Name: Delibird
Pokedex Entry: It carries food all day long. There are tales about lost people who were saved by the food it had.

Name: Mantine
Pokedex Entry: If it builds up enough speed swimming it can jump out above the waves and glide for over 300 feet.

Name: Skarmory
Pokedex Entry: Its sturdy heavy-looking iron body is actually thin and light so it can fly at speeds over 180 mph.

Name: Houndour
Pokedex Entry: It is smart enough to hunt in packs. It uses a variety of cries for communicating with others.

Name: Houndoom
Pokedex Entry: If you are burned by the flames it shoots from its mouth the pain will never go away.

Name: Kingdra
Pokedex Entry: It sleeps deep on the ocean floor to build its energy. It is said to cause tornadoes as it wakes.

Name: Phanpy
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon lives and nests on a riverbank. After playing in the mud it won’t be able to settle down unless it washes its body.

Name: Donphan
Pokedex Entry: Donphan is covered in tough hide so even being hit by a car won’t faze this Pokemon. However it is extremely susceptible to rain.

Name: Porygon2
Pokedex Entry: This artificial Pokemon evolved thanks to cutting-edge science. It sometimes displays behavior that is not in its programming.

Name: Stantler
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon apparently used to live in much harsher environments and thus it once had stronger psychic powers than it does now.

Name: Smeargle
Pokedex Entry: Once a Smeargle reaches adulthood it will have other members of its species leave paw prints on its back.

Name: Tyrogue
Pokedex Entry: This earnest Pokemon battles all sorts of opponents searching for the fighting style that suits it best.

Name: Hitmontop
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is adept at dance-like kicks. The horn atop its head is made from the same substance that generally forms fur and claws.

Name: Smoochum
Pokedex Entry: If its face gets even slightly dirty Smoochum will bathe immediately. But if its body gets dirty Smoochum doesn’t really seem to care.

Name: Elekid
Pokedex Entry: It loves violent thunder. The space between its horns flickers bluish white when it is charging energy.

Name: Magby
Pokedex Entry: Each and every time it inhales and exhales sparks leak from its mouth and nostrils.

Name: Miltank
Pokedex Entry: Miltank produces highly nutritious milk so it’s been supporting the lives of people and other Pokemon since ancient times.

Name: Blissey
Pokedex Entry: Anyone who takes even one taste of Blissey’s egg becomes unfailingly caring and pleasant to everyone.

Name: Raikou
Pokedex Entry: Raikou embodies the speed of lightning. The roars of this Pokemon send shock waves shuddering through the air and shake the ground as if lightning bolts had come crashing down.

Name: Entei
Pokedex Entry: Entei embodies the passion of magma. This Pokemon is thought to have been born in the eruption of a volcano. It sends up massive bursts of fire that utterly consume all that they touch.

Name: Suicune
Pokedex Entry: Suicune embodies the compassion of a pure spring of water. It runs across the land with gracefulness. This Pokemon has the power to purify dirty water.

Name: Larvitar
Pokedex Entry: Born deep underground this Pokemon becomes a pupa after eating enough dirt to make a mountain.

Name: Pupitar
Pokedex Entry: This pupa flies around wildly by venting with great force the gas pressurized inside its body.

Name: Tyranitar
Pokedex Entry: Extremely strong it can change the landscape. It is so insolent that it doesn’t care about others.

Name: Lugia
Pokedex Entry: Lugia’s wings pack devastating power—a light fluttering of its wings can blow apart regular houses. As a result this Pokemon chooses to live out of sight deep under the sea.

Name: Ho-oh
Pokedex Entry: Ho-Oh’s feathers glow in seven colors depending on the angle at which they are struck by light. These feathers are said to bring happiness to the bearers. This Pokemon is said to live at the foot of a rainbow.

Name: Celebi
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon came from the future by crossing over time. It is thought that so long as Celebi appears a bright and shining future awaits us.

Name: Treecko
Pokedex Entry: The small hooks on the soles of its feet latch on to walls and ceilings so it will never fall even while hanging upside down.

Name: Grovyle
Pokedex Entry: Its strongly developed thigh muscles give it astounding agility and jumping performance.

Name: Sceptile
Pokedex Entry: It agilely flits through the jungle and uses the sharp-edged leaves on its arms to cut down its prey.

Name: Torchic
Pokedex Entry: Torchic feels toasty warm if you hug it. It has a flame sac inside its belly and the flames burn continuously as long as Torchic has life in it.

Name: Combusken
Pokedex Entry: It boosts its concentration by emitting harsh cries. Its kicks have outstanding destructive power.

Name: Blaziken
Pokedex Entry: When facing a tough foe it looses flames from its wrists. Its powerful legs let it jump clear over buildings.

Name: Mudkip
Pokedex Entry: It has the power to crush large boulders into pieces. To rest it buries itself in mud at the bottom of a river.

Name: Marshtomp
Pokedex Entry: Living on muddy ground that provides poor footing has served to train its lower body and caused it to develop sturdy legs.

Name: Swampert
Pokedex Entry: Its arms are hard as rock. With one swing it can break an enormous boulder into pieces.

Name: Poochyena
Pokedex Entry: It bares its large fangs and barks vigorously to try to intimidate opponents but this is actually a manifestation of its cowardly nature.

Name: Mightyena
Pokedex Entry: They faithfully follow the orders of their leader. Prey targeted by Mightyena is never allowed to escape the outstanding teamwork of its pursuers.

Name: Zigzagoon
Pokedex Entry: It walks in zigzag fashion. It’s good at finding items in the grass and even in the ground.

Name: Linoone
Pokedex Entry: It charges prey at speeds over 60 mph. However because it can only run straight it often fails.

Name: Wurmple
Pokedex Entry: Using the spikes on its rear end Wurmple peels the bark off trees and feeds on the sap that oozes out. This Pokemon’s feet are tipped with suction pads that allow it to cling to glass without slipping.

Name: Silcoon
Pokedex Entry: Silcoon tethers itself to a tree branch using silk to keep from falling. There this Pokemon hangs quietly while it awaits evolution. It peers out of the silk cocoon through a small hole.

Name: Beautifly
Pokedex Entry: Beautifly’s favorite food is the sweet pollen of flowers. If you want to see this Pokemon just leave a potted flower by an open window. Beautifly is sure to come looking for pollen.

Name: Cascoon
Pokedex Entry: Cascoon makes its protective cocoon by wrapping its body entirely with a fine silk from its mouth. Once the silk goes around its body it hardens. This Pokemon prepares for its evolution inside the cocoon.

Name: Dustox
Pokedex Entry: Dustox is instinctively drawn to light. Swarms of this Pokemon are attracted by the bright lights of cities where they wreak havoc by stripping the leaves off roadside trees for food.

Name: Lotad
Pokedex Entry: The leaf on its head is naturally dirt repellent and will stay clean even after transporting Pokemon that are covered in mud.

Name: Lombre
Pokedex Entry: Old folklore in Kitakami tells of a mischievous child who was reborn as a Pokemon.

Name: Ludicolo
Pokedex Entry: There are structures throughout its whole body that produce energy when hit by sound waves with a cheerful rhythm.

Name: Seedot
Pokedex Entry: To expand its habitat it pretends to be a nut so that bird Pokemon will pick it up and carry it far away.

Name: Nuzleaf
Pokedex Entry: It leads a quiet life deep in the forest. If anything wanders into its territory Nuzleaf will warn the intruder by sounding its grass flute.

Name: Shiftry
Pokedex Entry: It is said that when Shiftry flaps its leafy fans atop ancient trees chilly winds blow and the season rolls into winter.

Name: Taillow
Pokedex Entry: Taillow courageously stands its ground against foes however strong they may be. This gutsy Pokemon will remain defiant even after a loss. On the other hand it cries loudly if it becomes hungry.

Name: Swellow
Pokedex Entry: Swellow flies high above our heads making graceful arcs in the sky. This Pokemon dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. The hapless prey is tightly grasped by Swellow’s clawed feet preventing escape.

Name: Wingull
Pokedex Entry: It soars high in the sky riding on updrafts like a glider. It carries food tucked in its bill.

Name: Pelipper
Pokedex Entry: It is a flying transporter that carries small Pokemon in its beak. It bobs on the waves to rest its wings.

Name: Ralts
Pokedex Entry: The horns on its head provide a strong power that enables it to sense people’s emotions.

Name: Kirlia
Pokedex Entry: It has a psychic power that enables it to distort the space around it and see into the future.

Name: Gardevoir
Pokedex Entry: To protect its Trainer it will expend all its psychic power to create a small black hole.

Name: Surskit
Pokedex Entry: They usually live on ponds but after an evening shower they may appear on puddles in towns.

Name: Masquerain
Pokedex Entry: It flaps its four wings to hover and fly freely in any direction—to and fro and sideways.

Name: Shroomish
Pokedex Entry: It prefers damp places. By day it remains still in the forest shade. It releases toxic powder from its head.

Name: Breloom
Pokedex Entry: It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.

Name: Slakoth
Pokedex Entry: It sleeps for 20 hours every day. Making drowsy those that see it is one of its abilities.

Name: Vigoroth
Pokedex Entry: Its stress level rises if it cannot keep moving constantly. Too much stress makes it feel sick.

Name: Slaking
Pokedex Entry: It is the world’s most slothful Pokemon. However it can exert horrifying power by releasing pent-up energy all at once.

Name: Nincada
Pokedex Entry: Because it lived almost entirely underground it is nearly blind. It uses its antennae instead.

Name: Ninjask
Pokedex Entry: Its cry leaves a lasting headache if heard for too long. It moves so quickly that it is almost invisible.

Name: Shedinja
Pokedex Entry: A most peculiar Pokemon that somehow appears in a Poke Ball when a Nincada evolves.

Name: Whismur
Pokedex Entry: The cry of a Whismur is over 100 decibels. If you’re close to a Whismur when it lets out a cry you’ll be stuck with an all-day headache.

Name: Loudred
Pokedex Entry: Loudred’s ears serve as speakers and they can put out sound waves powerful enough to blow away a house.

Name: Exploud
Pokedex Entry: In the past people would use the loud voices of these Pokemon as a means of communication between distant cities.

Name: Makuhita
Pokedex Entry: It grows stronger by enduring harsh training. It is a gutsy Pokemon that can withstand any attack.

Name: Hariyama
Pokedex Entry: It loves challenging others to tests of strength. It has the power to stop a train with a slap.

Name: Azurill
Pokedex Entry: Its tail bounces like a rubber ball. It flings that tail around to fight opponents bigger than itself.

Name: Nosepass
Pokedex Entry: The magnet in Nosepass’s nose provides an unerring compass making this Pokemon an excellent partner for Trainers going on a journey.

Name: Skitty
Pokedex Entry: Skitty has the habit of becoming fascinated by moving objects and chasing them around. This Pokemon is known to chase after its own tail and become dizzy.

Name: Delcatty
Pokedex Entry: Delcatty prefers to live an unfettered existence in which it can do as it pleases at its own pace. Because this Pokemon eats and sleeps whenever it decides its daily routines are completely random.

Name: Sableye
Pokedex Entry: It dwells in the darkness of caves. It uses its sharp claws to dig up gems to nourish itself.

Name: Mawile
Pokedex Entry: It uses its docile-looking face to lull foes into complacency then bites with its huge relentless jaws.

Name: Aron
Pokedex Entry: It eats iron ore—and sometimes railroad tracks— to build up the steel armor that protects its body.

Name: Lairon
Pokedex Entry: Lairon live in mountains brimming with spring water and iron ore so these Pokemon often came into conflict with humans in the past.

Name: Aggron
Pokedex Entry: Aggron has a horn sharp enough to perforate thick iron sheets. It brings down its opponents by ramming into them horn first.

Name: Meditite
Pokedex Entry: It never skips its daily yoga training. It heightens its inner strength through meditation.

Name: Medicham
Pokedex Entry: Through yoga training it gained the psychic power to predict its foe’s next move.

Name: Electrike
Pokedex Entry: It stores static electricity in its fur for discharging. It gives off sparks if a storm approaches.

Name: Manectric
Pokedex Entry: It stimulates its own muscles with electricity so it can move quickly. It eases its soreness with electricity too so it can recover quickly as well.

Name: Plusle
Pokedex Entry: It cheers on partners while scattering sparks from its body. It climbs telephone poles to absorb electricity.

Name: Minun
Pokedex Entry: Exposure to electricity from Minun and Plusle promotes blood circulation and relaxes muscles.

Name: Volbeat
Pokedex Entry: It lives around clean ponds. At night its rear lights up. It converses with others by flashing its light.

Name: Illumise
Pokedex Entry: Illumise uses its sweet scent to guide Volbeat having them form over 200 patterns in the night sky.

Name: Roselia
Pokedex Entry: Its flowers give off a relaxing fragrance. The stronger its aroma the healthier the Roselia is.

Name: Gulpin
Pokedex Entry: There is nothing its stomach can’t digest. While it is digesting vile overpowering gases are expelled.

Name: Swalot
Pokedex Entry: It gulps anything that fits in its mouth. Its special enzymes can dissolve anything.

Name: Carvanha
Pokedex Entry: It won’t attack while it’s alone—not even if it spots prey. Instead it waits for other Carvanha to join it and then the Pokemon attack as a group.

Name: Sharpedo
Pokedex Entry: As soon as it catches the scent of prey Sharpedo will jet seawater from its backside hurtling toward the target to attack at 75 mph.

Name: Wailmer
Pokedex Entry: It shows off by spraying jets of seawater from the nostrils above its eyes. It eats a solid ton of Wishiwashi every day.

Name: Wailord
Pokedex Entry: It can sometimes knock out opponents with the shock created by breaching and crashing its big body onto the water.

Name: Numel
Pokedex Entry: Magma of almost 2200 degrees Fahrenheit courses through its body. When it grows cold the magma hardens and slows it.

Name: Camerupt
Pokedex Entry: It lives in the crater of a volcano. It is well known that the humps on its back erupt every 10 years.

Name: Torkoal
Pokedex Entry: It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows out black soot if it is endangered.

Name: Spoink
Pokedex Entry: Spoink will die if it stops bouncing. The pearl on its head amplifies its psychic powers.

Name: Grumpig
Pokedex Entry: It can perform odd dance steps to influence foes. Its style of dancing became hugely popular overseas.

Name: Spinda
Pokedex Entry: Its steps are shaky and stumbling. Walking for a long time makes it feel sick.

Name: Trapinch
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon lives in arid deserts. It patiently awaits prey inside its funnel-shaped nest.

Name: Vibrava
Pokedex Entry: Rather than using its underdeveloped wings for flight it rubs them together emitting ultrasonic waves to attack its enemies.

Name: Flygon
Pokedex Entry: Known as the Desert Spirit this Pokemon hides in the sandstorms it causes by beating its wings.

Name: Cacnea
Pokedex Entry: It prefers harsh environments such as deserts. It can survive for 30 days on water stored in its body.

Name: Cacturne
Pokedex Entry: Packs of them follow travelers through the desert until the travelers can no longer move.

Name: Swablu
Pokedex Entry: It constantly grooms its cotton-like wings. It takes a shower to clean itself if it becomes dirty.

Name: Altaria
Pokedex Entry: If it bonds with a person it will gently envelop the friend with its soft wings then hum.

Name: Zangoose
Pokedex Entry: It’s Seviper’s archrival. To threaten those it encounters it fans out the claws on its front paws.

Name: Seviper
Pokedex Entry: It sharpens its swordlike tail on hard rocks. It hides in tall grass and strikes unwary prey with venomous fangs.

Name: Lunatone
Pokedex Entry: The phase of the moon apparently has some effect on its power. It’s active on the night of a full moon.

Name: Solrock
Pokedex Entry: When it rotates itself it gives off light similar to the sun thus blinding its foes.

Name: Barboach
Pokedex Entry: Its two whiskers provide a sensitive radar. Even in muddy waters it can detect its prey’s location.

Name: Whiscash
Pokedex Entry: It is extremely protective of its territory. If any foe approaches it attacks using vicious tremors.

Name: Corphish
Pokedex Entry: It came from overseas. It is a very hardy creature that will quickly proliferate even in polluted streams.

Name: Crawdaunt
Pokedex Entry: Loving to battle this Pokemon pinches all Pokemon that enter its territory with its pincers and throws them out.

Name: Baltoy
Pokedex Entry: It moves while spinning around on its single foot. Some Baltoy have been seen spinning on their heads.

Name: Claydol
Pokedex Entry: This mysterious Pokemon started life as an ancient clay figurine made over 20000 years ago.

Name: Lileep
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon was restored from a fossil. Lileep once lived in warm seas that existed approximately 100000000 years ago.

Name: Cradily
Pokedex Entry: It has short legs and can’t walk very fast but its neck and tentacles can extend to over three times their usual length to nab distant prey.

Name: Anorith
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon was restored from a fossil. Anorith lived in the ocean about 100000000 years ago hunting with its pair of claws.

Name: Armaldo
Pokedex Entry: After evolution this Pokemon emerged onto land. Its lower body has become stronger and blows from its tail are devastating.

Name: Feebas
Pokedex Entry: This tough Pokemon is perfectly fine even in dirty water. However due to its ragged shabby appearance it isn’t popular.

Name: Milotic
Pokedex Entry: Its lovely scales are described as rainbow-colored. They change color depending on the viewing angle.

Name: Castform
Pokedex Entry: Although its form changes with the weather that is apparently the result of a chemical reaction and not the result of its own free will.

Name: Kecleon
Pokedex Entry: It changes its hue to blend into its surroundings. If no one takes notice of it for too long it will pout and never reveal itself.

Name: Shuppet
Pokedex Entry: It loves to feed on feelings like envy and malice. Its upright horn catches the emotions of people.

Name: Banette
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon developed from an abandoned doll that amassed a grudge. It is seen in dark alleys.

Name: Duskull
Pokedex Entry: In the dead of night these Pokemon wander through towns in search of children whose vital energy is a Duskull’s favorite food.

Name: Dusclops
Pokedex Entry: Dusclops is feared because it’s said to pull the soul out of anyone who gazes upon the strange movements of its hands.

Name: Tropius
Pokedex Entry: It lives in tropical jungles. The bunch of fruit around its neck is delicious. The fruit grows twice a year.

Name: Chimecho
Pokedex Entry: It uses the sucker on its head to hang from a tree or from eaves. It can produce seven different tones.

Name: Absol
Pokedex Entry: Swift as the wind Absol races through fields and mountains. Its curved bow-like horn is acutely sensitive to the warning signs of natural disasters.

Name: Wynaut
Pokedex Entry: It tends to move in a pack. Individuals squash against one another to toughen their spirits.

Name: Snorunt
Pokedex Entry: It is said that several Snorunt gather under giant leaves and live together in harmony.

Name: Glalie
Pokedex Entry: Its prey is instantaneously frozen stiff by the cold air it exhales from its huge mouth. While they’re in that frozen state it gobbles them up.

Name: Spheal
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon’s body is covered in blubber and impressively round. It’s faster for Spheal to roll around than walk.

Name: Sealeo
Pokedex Entry: Sealeo live on top of drift ice. They go swimming when they’re on the hunt seeking out their prey by scent.

Name: Walrein
Pokedex Entry: Walrein form herds of 20 to 30 individuals. When a threat appears the herd’s leader will protect the group with its life.

Name: Clamperl
Pokedex Entry: Despite its appearance it’s carnivorous. It clamps down on its prey with both sides of its shell and doesn’t let go until they stop moving.

Name: Huntail
Pokedex Entry: It’s not the strongest swimmer. It wags its tail to lure in its prey and then gulps them down as soon as they get close.

Name: Gorebyss
Pokedex Entry: The color of its body changes with the water temperature. The coloration of Gorebyss in Alola is almost blindingly vivid.

Name: Relicanth
Pokedex Entry: Rock-hard scales and oil-filled swim bladders allow this Pokemon to survive the intense water pressure of the deep sea.

Name: Luvdisc
Pokedex Entry: Its heart-shaped body makes it popular. In some places you would give a Luvdisc to someone you love.

Name: Bagon
Pokedex Entry: Its steel-hard head can shatter boulders. It longingly hopes for wings to grow so it can fly.

Name: Shelgon
Pokedex Entry: The cells within its shell transform with explosive speed preparing it for evolution.

Name: Salamence
Pokedex Entry: It flies around on its wings which have grown in at last. In its happiness it gushes hot flames burning up everything it passes over.

Name: Beldum
Pokedex Entry: The magnetic force generated by its body repels the ground’s natural magnetism letting it float.

Name: Metang
Pokedex Entry: It is formed by two Beldum joining together. Its two brains are linked amplifying its psychic power.

Name: Metagross
Pokedex Entry: It folds its four legs when flying. Its four brains are said to be superior to a supercomputer.

Name: Regirock
Pokedex Entry: Every bit of Regirock’s body is made of stone. As parts of its body erode this Pokemon sticks rocks to itself to repair what’s been lost.

Name: Regice
Pokedex Entry: With cold air that can reach temperatures as low as −328 degrees Fahrenheit Regice instantly freezes any creature that approaches it.

Name: Registeel
Pokedex Entry: Registeel’s body is made of a strange material that is flexible enough to stretch and shrink but also more durable than any metal.

Name: Latias
Pokedex Entry: Latias is highly sensitive to the emotions of people. If it senses any hostility this Pokemon ruffles the feathers all over its body and cries shrilly to intimidate the foe.

Name: Latios
Pokedex Entry: Latios has the ability to make others see an image of what it has seen or imagines in its head. This Pokemon is intelligent and understands human speech.

Name: Kyogre
Pokedex Entry: Through Primal Reversion and with nature’s full power it will take back its true form. It can summon storms that cause the sea levels to rise.

Name: Groudon
Pokedex Entry: Groudon is said to be the personification of the land itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Kyogre as each sought to gain the power of nature.

Name: Rayquaza
Pokedex Entry: Rayquaza is said to have lived for hundreds of millions of years. Legends remain of how it put to rest the clash between Kyogre and Groudon.

Name: Jirachi
Pokedex Entry: A legend states that Jirachi will make true any wish that is written on notes attached to its head when it awakens. If this Pokemon senses danger it will fight without awakening.

Name: Deoxys
Pokedex Entry: The DNA of a space virus underwent a sudden mutation upon exposure to a laser beam and resulted in Deoxys. The crystalline organ on this Pokemon’s chest appears to be its brain.

Name: Turtwig
Pokedex Entry: The shell on its back is made of soil. If the shell is moist to the touch Turtwig is very healthy.

Name: Grotle
Pokedex Entry: Grotle live in the forest. Each is said to have its own secret place for getting clean springwater.

Name: Torterra
Pokedex Entry: Ancient people imagined that beneath the ground dwelt a gigantic Torterra.

Name: Chimchar
Pokedex Entry: It is very agile. Before going to sleep it extinguishes the flame on its tail to prevent fires.

Name: Monferno
Pokedex Entry: It skillfully controls the intensity of the fire on its tail to keep its foes at an ideal distance.

Name: Infernape
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon confounds opponents with its speed. It uses all its limbs to fight in its own unique style.

Name: Piplup
Pokedex Entry: A poor walker it often falls down. However its strong pride makes it puff up its chest without a care.

Name: Prinplup
Pokedex Entry: It lives a solitary life. Its wings deliver wicked blows that can snap even the thickest of trees in half with a single hit.

Name: Empoleon
Pokedex Entry: If anyone were to hurt its pride it would slash them in two with wings that can cleave through an ice floe.

Name: Starly
Pokedex Entry: They flock around mountains and fields chasing after bug Pokemon. Their singing is noisy and annoying.

Name: Staravia
Pokedex Entry: Recognizing their own weakness they always live in a group. When alone a Staravia cries noisily.

Name: Staraptor
Pokedex Entry: When Staravia evolve into Staraptor they leave the flock to live alone. They have sturdy wings.

Name: Bidoof
Pokedex Entry: With nerves of steel nothing can perturb it. It is more agile and active than it appears.

Name: Bibarel
Pokedex Entry: It busily makes its nest with stacks of branches and roots it has cut up with its sharp incisors.

Name: Kricketot
Pokedex Entry: Its legs are short. Whenever it stumbles its stiff antennae clack with a xylophone-like sound.

Name: Kricketune
Pokedex Entry: By allowing its cry to resonate in the hollow of its belly it produces a captivating sound.

Name: Shinx
Pokedex Entry: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. It glows when in trouble.

Name: Luxio
Pokedex Entry: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.

Name: Luxray
Pokedex Entry: It can see clearly through walls to track down its prey and seek its lost young.

Name: Budew
Pokedex Entry: The pollen it releases contains poison. If this Pokemon is raised on clean water the poison’s toxicity is increased.

Name: Roserade
Pokedex Entry: After captivating opponents with its sweet scent it lashes them with its thorny whips.

Name: Cranidos
Pokedex Entry: It lived in jungles around a hundred million years ago. It used its skillful headbutts to combat Aerodactyl.

Name: Rampardos
Pokedex Entry: Stifled by a thick skull that can withstand any impact this Pokemon’s brain never got very big.

Name: Shieldon
Pokedex Entry: It is outstandingly armored. As a result it has no particular need to battle with others and can spend its time feeding on grass and berries.

Name: Bastiodon
Pokedex Entry: While it can guard against any sort of attack from the front it is left without recourse when attacked from behind.

Name: Burmy
Pokedex Entry: To shelter itself from cold wintry winds it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.

Name: Wormadam
Pokedex Entry: Its appearance changes depending on where it evolved. The materials on hand become a part of its body.

Name: Mothim
Pokedex Entry: It loves the honey of flowers and steals honey collected by Combee.

Name: Combee
Pokedex Entry: At night Combee sleep in a group of about a hundred packed closely together in a lump.

Name: Vespiquen
Pokedex Entry: It houses its colony in cells in its body and releases various pheromones to make those grubs do its bidding.

Name: Pachirisu
Pokedex Entry: It’s one of the kinds of Pokemon with electric cheek pouches. It shoots charges from its tail.

Name: Buizel
Pokedex Entry: It spins its two tails like a screw to propel itself through water. The tails also slice clinging seaweed.

Name: Floatzel
Pokedex Entry: With its flotation sac inflated it can carry people on its back. It deflates the sac before it dives.

Name: Cherubi
Pokedex Entry: It nimbly dashes about to avoid getting pecked by bird Pokemon that would love to make off with its small nutrient-rich storage ball.

Name: Cherrim
Pokedex Entry: As a bud it barely moves. It sits still placidly waiting for sunlight to appear.

Name: Shellos
Pokedex Entry: It used to have a shell on its back long ago. This species is closely related to Pokemon like Shellder.

Name: Gastrodon
Pokedex Entry: Its whole body is sticky with mucus. In the past this form of Gastrodon was by far the more numerous one.

Name: Ambipom
Pokedex Entry: They live on large trees. They are said to communicate by connecting their tails to those of others.

Name: Drifloon
Pokedex Entry: It is whispered that any child who mistakes Drifloon for a balloon and holds on to it could wind up missing.

Name: Drifblim
Pokedex Entry: It can generate and release gas within its body. That’s how it can control the altitude of its drift.

Name: Buneary
Pokedex Entry: If both of Buneary’s ears are rolled up something is wrong with its body or mind. It’s a sure sign the Pokemon is in need of care.

Name: Lopunny
Pokedex Entry: Lopunny is constantly monitoring its surroundings. If danger approaches this Pokemon responds with superdestructive kicks.

Name: Mismagius
Pokedex Entry: Its cry sounds like an incantation. It is said the cry may rarely be imbued with happiness-giving power.

Name: Honchkrow
Pokedex Entry: It is merciless by nature. It is said that it never forgives the mistakes of its Murkrow followers.

Name: Glameow
Pokedex Entry: It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate. Its fickleness is very popular among some.

Name: Purugly
Pokedex Entry: It would claim another Pokemon’s nest as its own if it finds a nest sufficiently comfortable.

Name: Chingling
Pokedex Entry: There is an orb inside its mouth. When it hops the orb bounces all over and makes a ringing sound.

Name: Stunky
Pokedex Entry: It sprays a foul fluid from its rear. Its stench spreads over a mile radius driving Pokemon away.

Name: Skuntank
Pokedex Entry: It attacks by spraying a horribly smelly fluid from the tip of its tail. Attacks from above confound it.

Name: Bronzor
Pokedex Entry: Ancient people believed that the pattern on Bronzor’s back contained a mysterious power.

Name: Bronzong
Pokedex Entry: In ages past this Pokemon was revered as a bringer of rain. It was found buried in the ground.

Name: Bonsly
Pokedex Entry: In order to adjust the level of fluids in its body it exudes water from its eyes. This makes it appear to be crying.

Name: Mime Jr.
Pokedex Entry: It mimics everyone it sees but it puts extra effort into copying the graceful dance steps of Mr. Rime as practice.

Name: Happiny
Pokedex Entry: It carries a round white rock in its belly pouch. If it gets along well with someone it will sometimes give that person the rock.

Name: Chatot
Pokedex Entry: It mimics the cries of other Pokemon to trick them into thinking it’s one of them. This way they won’t attack it.

Name: Spiritomb
Pokedex Entry: Its constant mischief and misdeeds resulted in it being bound to an Odd Keystone by a mysterious spell.

Name: Gible
Pokedex Entry: It skulks in caves and when prey or an enemy passes by it leaps out and chomps them. The force of its attack sometimes chips its teeth.

Name: Gabite
Pokedex Entry: In rare cases it molts and sheds its scales. Medicine containing its scales as an ingredient will make a weary body feel invigorated.

Name: Garchomp
Pokedex Entry: It is said that when one runs at high speed its wings create blades of wind that can fell nearby trees.

Name: Munchlax
Pokedex Entry: It needs to consume its own weight in food every day. As far as flavor is concerned it’s indifferent.

Name: Riolu
Pokedex Entry: They communicate with one another using their auras. They are able to run all through the night.

Name: Lucario
Pokedex Entry: It’s said that no foe can remain invisible to Lucario since it can detect auras—even those of foes it could not otherwise see.

Name: Hippopotas
Pokedex Entry: It shuts its nostrils tight then travels through sand as if walking. They form colonies of around 10.

Name: Hippowdon
Pokedex Entry: It is surprisingly quick to anger. It holds its mouth agape as a display of its strength.

Name: Skorupi
Pokedex Entry: After burrowing into the sand it waits patiently for prey to come near. This Pokemon and Sizzlipede share common descent.

Name: Drapion
Pokedex Entry: Its poison is potent but it rarely sees use. This Pokemon prefers to use physical force instead going on rampages with its car-crushing strength.

Name: Croagunk
Pokedex Entry: Inflating its poison sacs it fills the area with an odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a poison jab.

Name: Toxicroak
Pokedex Entry: Swaying and dodging the attacks of its foes it weaves its flexible body in close then lunges out with its poisonous claws.

Name: Carnivine
Pokedex Entry: It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling saliva then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.

Name: Finneon
Pokedex Entry: The line running down its side can store sunlight. It shines vividly at night.

Name: Lumineon
Pokedex Entry: With its shining light it lures its prey close. However the light also happens to attract ferocious fish Pokemon—its natural predators.

Name: Mantyke
Pokedex Entry: Mantyke living in Galar seem to be somewhat sluggish. The colder waters of the seas in this region may be the cause.

Name: Snover
Pokedex Entry: During cold seasons it migrates to the mountain’s lower reaches. It returns to the snow-covered summit in the spring.

Name: Abomasnow
Pokedex Entry: It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.

Name: Weavile
Pokedex Entry: Evolution made it even more devious. It communicates by clawing signs in boulders.

Name: Magnezone
Pokedex Entry: As it zooms through the sky this Pokemon seems to be receiving signals of unknown origin while transmitting signals of unknown purpose.

Name: Lickilicky
Pokedex Entry: Lickilicky’s strange tongue can stretch to many times the length of its body. No one has figured out how Lickilicky’s tongue can stretch so far.

Name: Rhyperior
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon’s sturdy carapace protects it from volcanic eruptions. It shoots round rocks from the holes in its hands.

Name: Tangrowth
Pokedex Entry: Tangrowth has two arms that it can extend as it pleases. Recent research has shown that these arms are in fact bundles of vines.

Name: Electivire
Pokedex Entry: When it gets excited it thumps its chest. With every thud thunder roars and electric sparks shower all around.

Name: Magmortar
Pokedex Entry: When shooting 3600 degree Fahrenheit fireballs from its arms its body takes on a whitish hue from the intense heat.

Name: Togekiss
Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are never seen anywhere near conflict or turmoil. In recent times they’ve hardly been seen at all.

Name: Yanmega
Pokedex Entry: Yanmega’s wingbeats are so powerful that the Pokemon blows down huge trees nearby when it vigorously launches itself into flight.

Name: Leafeon
Pokedex Entry: When you see Leafeon asleep in a patch of sunshine you’ll know it is using photosynthesis to produce clean air.

Name: Glaceon
Pokedex Entry: It can control its body temperature at will. This enables it to freeze the moisture in the atmosphere creating flurries of diamond dust.

Name: Gliscor
Pokedex Entry: If it succeeds in catching even a faint breeze properly it can circle the globe without flapping once.

Name: Mamoswine
Pokedex Entry: A frozen Mamoswine was dug from ice dating back 10000 years. This Pokemon has been around a long long long time.

Name: Porygon-Z
Pokedex Entry: An additional program was installed to create a more advanced Pokemon but it was apparently flawed. Porygon-Z moves oddly as a result.

Name: Gallade
Pokedex Entry: When trying to protect someone it extends its elbows as if they were swords and fights savagely.

Name: Probopass
Pokedex Entry: It controls three units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force. With them it can attack a foe from three directions.

Name: Dusknoir
Pokedex Entry: It is said to take lost spirits into its pliant body and take them to the afterlife.

Name: Froslass
Pokedex Entry: When it finds humans or Pokemon it likes it freezes them and takes them to its chilly den where they become decorations.

Name: Rotom
Pokedex Entry: Its electricity-like body can enter some kinds of machines and take control in order to make mischief.

Name: Uxie
Pokedex Entry: Known as “The Being of Knowledge.” It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.

Name: Mesprit
Pokedex Entry: Known as “The Being of Emotion.” It taught humans the nobility of sorrow pain and joy.

Name: Azelf
Pokedex Entry: Known as “The Being of Willpower.” It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.

Name: Dialga
Pokedex Entry: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.

Name: Palkia
Pokedex Entry: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.

Name: Heatran
Pokedex Entry: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

Name: Regigigas
Pokedex Entry: It is said to have made Pokemon that look like itself from a special ice mountain rocks and magma.

Name: Giratina
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours where common knowledge is distorted and strange.

Name: Cresselia
Pokedex Entry: When it flies it releases shiny particles from its veil-like wings. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

Name: Phione
Pokedex Entry: When the water warms they inflate the flotation sac on their heads and drift languidly on the sea in packs.

Name: Manaphy
Pokedex Entry: It is born with a wondrous power that lets it bond with any kind of Pokemon.

Name: Darkrai
Pokedex Entry: It chases people and Pokemon from its territory by causing them to experience deep nightmarish slumbers.

Name: Shaymin
Pokedex Entry: It can dissolve toxins in the air to instantly transform ruined land into a lush field of flowers.

Name: Arceus
Pokedex Entry: According to the legends of Sinnoh this Pokemon emerged from an egg and shaped all there is in this world.

Name: Victini
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win regardless of the type of encounter.

Name: Snivy
Pokedex Entry: The leaf on Snivy’s tail generates energy when exposed to sunlight making Snivy swifter and adding an edge to its moves.

Name: Servine
Pokedex Entry: It runs low to the ground weaving through the grass then mercilessly pummels its target by whipping them with its vines.

Name: Serperior
Pokedex Entry: It generates energy from sunlight then amplifies that energy dozens of times within its long body.

Name: Tepig
Pokedex Entry: It’s more nimble than it looks and it uses its speed to confound its enemies. It rapidly launches fireballs from both nostrils.

Name: Pignite
Pokedex Entry: When Pignite enters battle its body temperature rapidly soars until Pignite itself is engulfed by a scorching fireball.

Name: Emboar
Pokedex Entry: The flames blazing deep inside Emboar’s chest erupt vigorously from its chin forming a beard of fire.

Name: Oshawott
Pokedex Entry: It wields the scalchop on its stomach like a knife blocking the moves of its enemies before slashing back at them in swift retaliation.

Name: Dewott
Pokedex Entry: It’s said that people modeled swordplay after the way Dewott’s movements flow like water while it’s wielding its two scalchops.

Name: Samurott
Pokedex Entry: A master of a sword-drawing art called iaijutsu Samurott settles its battles with a single swing of either large sword sheathed in its foreleg armor.

Name: Patrat
Pokedex Entry: Using food stored in cheek pouches they can keep watch for days. They use their tails to communicate with others.

Name: Watchog
Pokedex Entry: Using luminescent matter it makes its eyes and body glow and stuns attacking opponents.

Name: Lillipup
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is courageous but also cautious. It uses the soft fur covering its face to collect information about its surroundings.

Name: Herdier
Pokedex Entry: Herdier is a very smart and friendly Pokemon. So much so that there’s a theory that Herdier was the first Pokemon to partner with people.

Name: Stoutland
Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon seem to enjoy living with humans. Even a Stoutland caught in the wild will warm up to people in about three days.

Name: Purrloin
Pokedex Entry: It steals things from people just to amuse itself with their frustration. A rivalry exists between this Pokemon and Nickit.

Name: Liepard
Pokedex Entry: Don’t be fooled by its gorgeous fur and elegant figure. This is a moody and vicious Pokemon.

Name: Pansage
Pokedex Entry: It shares the leaf on its head with weary-looking Pokemon. These leaves are known to relieve stress.

Name: Simisage
Pokedex Entry: It attacks enemies with strikes of its thorn-covered tail. This Pokemon is wild tempered.

Name: Pansear
Pokedex Entry: Very intelligent it roasts berries before eating them. It likes to help people.

Name: Simisear
Pokedex Entry: A flame burns inside its body. It scatters embers from its head and tail to sear its opponents.

Name: Panpour
Pokedex Entry: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. It waters plants with it using its tail.

Name: Simipour
Pokedex Entry: The high-pressure water expelled from its tail is so powerful it can destroy a concrete wall.

Name: Munna
Pokedex Entry: Late at night it appears beside people’s pillows. As it feeds on dreams the patterns on its body give off a faint glow.

Name: Musharna
Pokedex Entry: When dark mists emanate from its body don’t get too near. If you do your nightmares will become reality.

Name: Pidove
Pokedex Entry: Where people go these Pokemon follow. If you’re scattering food for them be careful—several hundred of them can gather at once.

Name: Tranquill
Pokedex Entry: It can fly moderately quickly. No matter how far it travels it can always find its way back to its master and its nest.

Name: Unfezant
Pokedex Entry: Unfezant are exceptional fliers. The females are known for their stamina while the males outclass them in terms of speed.

Name: Blitzle
Pokedex Entry: Its heartbeat generates electricity. When Blitzle is surprised and its heart rate goes up the voltage of its electricity also rises.

Name: Zebstrika
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is aggressive and has a volatile disposition. When agitated it will illuminate its mane in yellow and fire off bolts of electricity.

Name: Roggenrola
Pokedex Entry: It’s as hard as steel but apparently a long soak in water will cause it to soften a bit.

Name: Boldore
Pokedex Entry: If you see its orange crystals start to glow be wary. It’s about to fire off bursts of energy.

Name: Gigalith
Pokedex Entry: This hardy Pokemon can often be found on construction sites and in mines working alongside people and Copperajah.

Name: Woobat
Pokedex Entry: While inside a cave if you look up and see lots of heart-shaped marks lining the walls it’s evidence that Woobat live there.

Name: Swoobat
Pokedex Entry: Emitting powerful sound waves tires it out. Afterward it won’t be able to fly for a little while.

Name: Drilbur
Pokedex Entry: It can dig through the ground at a speed of 30 mph. It could give a car running aboveground a good race.

Name: Excadrill
Pokedex Entry: Forming a drill with its steel claws and head it can bore through a steel plate no matter how thick it is.

Name: Audino
Pokedex Entry: Audino’s sense of hearing is superb. Not even a pebble rolling along over a mile away will escape Audino’s ears.

Name: Timburr
Pokedex Entry: Always carrying squared logs they help out with construction. As they grow they carry bigger logs.

Name: Gurdurr
Pokedex Entry: They strengthen their bodies by carrying steel beams. They show off their big muscles to their friends.

Name: Conkeldurr
Pokedex Entry: It is thought that Conkeldurr taught humans how to make concrete more than 2000 years ago.

Name: Tympole
Pokedex Entry: Graceful ripples running across the water’s surface are a sure sign that Tympole are singing in high-pitched voices below.

Name: Palpitoad
Pokedex Entry: It weakens its prey with sound waves intense enough to cause headaches then entangles them with its sticky tongue.

Name: Seismitoad
Pokedex Entry: The vibrating of the bumps all over its body causes earthquake-like tremors. Seismitoad and Croagunk are similar species.

Name: Throh
Pokedex Entry: It performs throwing moves with first-rate skill. Over the course of many battles Throh’s belt grows darker as it absorbs its wearer’s sweat.

Name: Sawk
Pokedex Entry: If you see a Sawk training in the mountains in its single-minded pursuit of strength it’s best to quietly pass by.

Name: Sewaddle
Pokedex Entry: Sewaddle chews on leaves to make its clothing. It’s trying to mimic the leafy garment Leavanny first dressed it in.

Name: Swadloon
Pokedex Entry: Swadloon lives quietly at the feet of trees. It prefers eating fallen leaves that have grown soft rather than fresh ones.

Name: Leavanny
Pokedex Entry: This gentle Pokemon has strong protective instincts. The leaves on its arms are sharp enough to slice a thick tree in half with one stroke.

Name: Venipede
Pokedex Entry: Venipede and Sizzlipede are similar species but when the two meet a huge fight ensues.

Name: Whirlipede
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon spins itself rapidly and charges into its opponents. Its top speed is just over 60 mph.

Name: Scolipede
Pokedex Entry: Scolipede latches on to its prey with the claws on its neck before slamming them into the ground and jabbing them with its claws’ toxic spikes.

Name: Cottonee
Pokedex Entry: Pillows and beds stuffed with cotton exhaled by Cottonee are soft and puffy light and airy—altogether top quality.

Name: Whimsicott
Pokedex Entry: Like the wind it can slip through any gap no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.

Name: Petilil
Pokedex Entry: The leaves on its head grow right back even if they fall out. These bitter leaves refresh those who eat them.

Name: Lilligant
Pokedex Entry: The fragrance of the garland on its head has a relaxing effect but taking care of it is very difficult.

Name: Basculin
Pokedex Entry: Its temperament is vicious and aggressive. This Pokemon is also full of vitality and can multiply rapidly before anyone notices.

Name: Sandile
Pokedex Entry: It submerges itself in sand and moves as if swimming. This wise behavior keeps its enemies from finding it and maintains its temperature.

Name: Krokorok
Pokedex Entry: Protected by thin membranes their eyes can see even in the dead of night. They live in groups of a few individuals.

Name: Krookodile
Pokedex Entry: After clamping down with its powerful jaws it twists its body around to rip its prey in half.

Name: Darumaka
Pokedex Entry: Darumaka’s droppings are hot so people used to put them in their clothes to keep themselves warm.

Name: Darmanitan
Pokedex Entry: When one is injured in a fierce battle it hardens into a stone-like form. Then it meditates and sharpens its mind.

Name: Maractus
Pokedex Entry: With noises that could be mistaken for the rattles of maracas it creates an upbeat rhythm startling bird Pokemon and making them fly off in a hurry.

Name: Dwebble
Pokedex Entry: When it finds a stone appealing it creates a hole inside it and uses it as its home. This Pokemon is the natural enemy of Roggenrola and Rolycoly.

Name: Crustle
Pokedex Entry: This highly territorial Pokemon prefers dry climates. It won’t come out of its boulder on rainy days.

Name: Scraggy
Pokedex Entry: It stretches its saggy skin up to its neck to protect itself. Among Scraggy individuals with saggier skin apparently garner more respect.

Name: Scrafty
Pokedex Entry: Groups of them beat up anything that enters their territory. Each can spit acidic liquid from its mouth.

Name: Sigilyph
Pokedex Entry: Psychic power allows these Pokemon to fly. Some say they were the guardians of an ancient city. Others say they were the guardians’ emissaries.

Name: Yamask
Pokedex Entry: It wanders through ruins by night carrying a mask that’s said to have been the face it had when it was still human.

Name: Cofagrigus
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon has a body of sparkling gold. People say it no longer remembers that it was once human.

Name: Tirtouga
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon inhabited ancient seas. Although it can only crawl it still comes up onto land in search of prey.

Name: Carracosta
Pokedex Entry: Carracosta completely devours its prey—bones shells and all. Because of this Carracosta’s own shell grows thick and sturdy.

Name: Archen
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon was successfully restored from a fossil. As research suggested Archen is unable to fly. But it’s very good at jumping.

Name: Archeops
