Pokedex Entry: It needs a running start to take off. If Archeops wants to fly it first needs to run nearly 25 mph building speed over a course of about 2.5 miles.

Name: Trubbish
Pokedex Entry: Its favorite places are unsanitary ones. If you leave trash lying around you could even find one of these Pokemon living in your room.

Name: Garbodor
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon eats trash which turns into poison inside its body. The main component of the poison depends on what sort of trash was eaten.

Name: Zorua
Pokedex Entry: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently it often transforms into a silent child.

Name: Zoroark
Pokedex Entry: Stories say those who tried to catch Zoroark were trapped in an illusion and punished.

Name: Minccino
Pokedex Entry: When its tail has gotten dirty from self-cleaning or from cleaning its nest Minccino spends a whole day washing its tail in clean springwater.

Name: Cinccino
Pokedex Entry: Their white fur is coated in a special oil that makes it easy for them to deflect attacks.

Name: Gothita
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is normally very innocent. When it is staring at something invisible it is unblinking and utterly silent.

Name: Gothorita
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon will hypnotize children to put them to sleep before carrying them away. Be wary of nights when the starlight is bright.

Name: Gothitelle
Pokedex Entry: Gothitelle unleashes psychic energy and shows opponents dreams of the universe’s end. These dreams are apparently ethereal and beautiful.

Name: Solosis
Pokedex Entry: Because their bodies are enveloped in a special liquid they can survive in any environment.

Name: Duosion
Pokedex Entry: Since they have two divided brains at times they suddenly try to take two different actions at once.

Name: Reuniclus
Pokedex Entry: Their arms are made of a special liquid. They use psychic power to control these arms and crush boulders.

Name: Ducklett
Pokedex Entry: It’s not very good at flying yet. It watches the dances of its Swanna parents to learn how to move its wings.

Name: Swanna
Pokedex Entry: Centered around its leader the flock dances in perfect sync to strengthen its unity.

Name: Vanillite
Pokedex Entry: Unable to survive in hot areas it makes itself comfortable by breathing out air cold enough to cause snow. It burrows into the snow to sleep.

Name: Vanillish
Pokedex Entry: By drinking pure water it grows its icy body. This Pokemon can be hard to find on days with warm sunny weather.

Name: Vanilluxe
Pokedex Entry: When its anger reaches a breaking point this Pokemon unleashes a fierce blizzard that freezes every creature around it be they friend or foe.

Name: Deerling
Pokedex Entry: Deerling have different scents depending on the season. In early spring these Pokemon give off a delicate sweet and calming scent.

Name: Sawsbuck
Pokedex Entry: It seems that a Sawsbuck with many flowers on its antlers will grow at a slightly slower pace because the flowers absorb the Pokemon’s nutrients.

Name: Emolga
Pokedex Entry: As Emolga flutters through the air it crackles with electricity. This Pokemon is cute but it can cause a lot of trouble.

Name: Karrablast
Pokedex Entry: Its strange physiology reacts to electrical energy in interesting ways. The presence of a Shelmet will cause this Pokemon to evolve.

Name: Escavalier
Pokedex Entry: They use shells they’ve stolen from Shelmet to arm and protect themselves. They’re very popular Pokemon in the Galar region.

Name: Foongus
Pokedex Entry: There is a theory that the developer of the modern-day Poke Ball really liked Foongus but this has not been confirmed.

Name: Amoonguss
Pokedex Entry: Be wary of the poisonous spores it releases. Mushrooms resembling Amoonguss’s caps will grow out of anywhere the spores touch.

Name: Frillish
Pokedex Entry: It envelops its prey in its veillike arms and draws it down to the deeps five miles below the ocean’s surface.

Name: Jellicent
Pokedex Entry: Most of this Pokemon’s body composition is identical to sea water. It makes sunken ships its lair.

Name: Alomomola
Pokedex Entry: It gently holds injured and weak Pokemon in its fins. Its special membrane heals their wounds.

Name: Joltik
Pokedex Entry: Joltik that live in cities have learned a technique for sucking electricity from the outlets in houses.

Name: Galvantula
Pokedex Entry: They employ an electrically charged web to trap their prey. While it is immobilized by shock they leisurely consume it.

Name: Ferroseed
Pokedex Entry: It defends itself by launching spikes but its aim isn’t very good at first. Only after a lot of practice will it improve.

Name: Ferrothorn
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon scrapes its spikes across rocks and then uses the tips of its feelers to absorb the nutrients it finds within the stone.

Name: Klink
Pokedex Entry: The two minigears that compose this Pokemon are closer than twins. They mesh well only with each other.

Name: Klang
Pokedex Entry: When Klang goes all out the minigear links up perfectly with the outer part of the big gear and this Pokemon’s rotation speed increases sharply.

Name: Klinklang
Pokedex Entry: From its spikes it launches powerful blasts of electricity. Its red core contains an enormous amount of energy.

Name: Tynamo
Pokedex Entry: While one alone doesn’t have much power a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.

Name: Eelektrik
Pokedex Entry: They coil around foes and shock them with electricity-generating organs that seem simply to be circular patterns.

Name: Eelektross
Pokedex Entry: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

Name: Elgyem
Pokedex Entry: If this Pokemon stands near a TV strange scenery will appear on the screen. That scenery is said to be from its home.

Name: Beheeyem
Pokedex Entry: Whenever a Beheeyem visits a farm a Dubwool mysteriously disappears.

Name: Litwick
Pokedex Entry: Its flame is usually out but it starts shining when Litwick absorbs life-force from people or Pokemon.

Name: Lampent
Pokedex Entry: Lampent appears at the moment of death and promptly absorbs the spirit as it leaves the body.

Name: Chandelure
Pokedex Entry: The spirits burned up in its ominous flame lose their way and wander this world forever.

Name: Axew
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon lives in nests that are made in the ground. People in ancient times used its tusks as cooking knives.

Name: Fraxure
Pokedex Entry: Because its tusks don’t grow back once they break this Pokemon apparently won’t use them unless truly necessary.

Name: Haxorus
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon nests in caves and abandoned mines. It is docile but it will become incredibly angry if its tusks are touched so beware.

Name: Cubchoo
Pokedex Entry: Many of this species can be found along the shorelines of cold regions. If a Cubchoo lacks dangling snot there’s a chance it is sick.

Name: Beartic
Pokedex Entry: It is a ferocious carnivorous Pokemon. Once it captures its prey it will breathe cold air onto the prey to freeze and preserve it.

Name: Cryogonal
Pokedex Entry: Cryogonal appear during cold seasons. It is said that people and Pokemon who die on snowy mountains are reborn into these Pokemon.

Name: Shelmet
Pokedex Entry: When attacked it tightly shuts the lid of its shell. This reaction fails to protect it from Karrablast however because they can still get into the shell.

Name: Accelgor
Pokedex Entry: It moves with blinding speed and lobs poison at foes. Featuring Accelgor as a main character is a surefire way to make a movie or comic popular.

Name: Stunfisk
Pokedex Entry: Its skin is very hard so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity.

Name: Mienfoo
Pokedex Entry: In fights they dominate with onslaughts of flowing continuous attacks. With their sharp claws they cut enemies.

Name: Mienshao
Pokedex Entry: When Mienshao lets out a bizarre wail you’re in danger. A flurry of kicks and chops too fast to see is about to be unleashed!

Name: Druddigon
Pokedex Entry: Druddigon lives in caves but it never skips sunbathing—it won’t be able to move if its body gets too cold.

Name: Golett
Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon are thought to have been created by the science of an ancient and mysterious civilization.

Name: Golurk
Pokedex Entry: When the seal on its chest is removed it rages indiscriminately. During such rampages it can turn a whole town into a mountain of rubble.

Name: Pawniard
Pokedex Entry: Pawniard will fearlessly challenge even powerful foes. In a pinch it will cling to opponents and pierce them with the blades all over its body.

Name: Bisharp
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon commands a group of several Pawniard. Groups that are defeated in territorial disputes are absorbed by the winning side.

Name: Bouffalant
Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon can crush a car with no more than a headbutt. Bouffalant with more hair on their heads hold higher positions within the herd.

Name: Rufflet
Pokedex Entry: They pick fights indiscriminately. They grow stronger and more powerful each time they faint or are injured.

Name: Braviary
Pokedex Entry: The more scars they have the more respect these brave soldiers of the sky get from their peers.

Name: Vullaby
Pokedex Entry: They tend to guard their posteriors with suitable bones they have found. They pursue weak Pokemon.

Name: Mandibuzz
Pokedex Entry: It’s always searching for food for Vullaby. When it finds a weak Pokemon Mandibuzz swoops it right off to its nest.

Name: Heatmor
Pokedex Entry: There’s a hole in its tail that allows it to draw in the air it needs to keep its fire burning. If the hole gets blocked this Pokemon will fall ill.

Name: Durant
Pokedex Entry: They lay their eggs deep inside their nests. When attacked by Heatmor they retaliate using their massive mandibles.

Name: Deino
Pokedex Entry: It can’t see so its first approach to examining things is to bite them. You will be covered in wounds until a Deino warms up to you.

Name: Zweilous
Pokedex Entry: The two heads do not get along at all. If you don’t give each head the same amount of attention they’ll begin fighting out of jealousy.

Name: Hydreigon
Pokedex Entry: Only the central head has a brain. It is very intelligent but it thinks only of destruction.

Name: Larvesta
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon was called the Larva That Stole the Sun. The fire Larvesta spouts from its horns can cut right through a sheet of iron.

Name: Volcarona
Pokedex Entry: Its burning body causes it to be unpopular in hot parts of the world but in cold ones Volcarona is revered as an embodiment of the sun.

Name: Cobalion
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon appears in a legend alongside Terrakion and Virizion fighting against humans in defense of the Unova region’s Pokemon.

Name: Terrakion
Pokedex Entry: It has phenomenal power. It will mercilessly crush anyone or anything that bullies small Pokemon.

Name: Virizion
Pokedex Entry: A legend tells of this Pokemon working together with Cobalion and Terrakion to protect the Pokemon of the Unova region.

Name: Tornadus
Pokedex Entry: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.

Name: Thundurus
Pokedex Entry: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.

Name: Reshiram
Pokedex Entry: This legendary Pokemon can scorch the world with fire. It helps those who want to build a world of truth.

Name: Zekrom
Pokedex Entry: This legendary Pokemon can scorch the world with lightning. It assists those who want to build an ideal world.

Name: Landorus
Pokedex Entry: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as “The Guardian of the Fields.”

Name: Kyurem
Pokedex Entry: This legendary ice Pokemon waits for a hero to fill in the missing parts of its body with truth or ideals.

Name: Keldeo
Pokedex Entry: It crosses the world running over the surfaces of oceans and rivers. It appears at scenic waterfronts.

Name: Meloetta
Pokedex Entry: The melodies sung by Meloetta have the power to make Pokemon that hear them happy or sad.

Name: Genesect
Pokedex Entry: This ancient bug Pokemon was altered by Team Plasma. They upgraded the cannon on its back.

Name: Chespin
Pokedex Entry: When Chespin tenses up just before landing a headbutt the spikes on its head sharpen to points piercing the enemy’s body on contact.

Name: Quilladin
Pokedex Entry: It’s protected by a sturdy shell. The shell is also very heavy which naturally strengthens Quilladin’s lower body.

Name: Chesnaught
Pokedex Entry: When its allies are in trouble Chesnaught creates a shield with its arms and uses its own body to block attacks.

Name: Fennekin
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon gets worked up easily. Its body can also overheat so it uses its ears to dissipate the heat and calm down.

Name: Braixen
Pokedex Entry: It ignites the twig from its tail and waves the twig around to signal its allies. To indicate danger it draws circles in the air with the twig’s flame.

Name: Delphox
Pokedex Entry: It leaves burn marks in the ground with the flame at the tip of its wand. Long ago people used the shapes of these burn marks for divination.

Name: Froakie
Pokedex Entry: Its happy-go-lucky look is an act intended to fool its enemies. It will suddenly drop the facade and overwhelm its foes with its blinding speed.

Name: Frogadier
Pokedex Entry: It excels at devising battle strategies that make use of the terrain and it never misses its mark when throwing bubble-covered pebbles.

Name: Greninja
Pokedex Entry: The movement of air against the long tongue Greninja keeps wrapped around its neck allows it to sense enemies it can’t see.

Name: Bunnelby
Pokedex Entry: It excels at digging holes. Using its ears it can dig a nest 33 feet deep in one night.

Name: Diggersby
Pokedex Entry: With power equal to an excavator it can dig through dense bedrock. It’s a huge help during tunnel construction.

Name: Fletchling
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is normally calm but once it enters battle its hormonal balance changes and it becomes aggressive.

Name: Fletchinder
Pokedex Entry: Fletchinder scatters embers in tall grass where bug Pokemon might be hiding and then catches them as they come leaping out.

Name: Talonflame
Pokedex Entry: It has top-notch flying capabilities. It flies around easily even while carrying prey that weighs more than 220 lbs.

Name: Scatterbug
Pokedex Entry: Any poison this Pokemon takes in is converted into a black powder and secreted. That’s why Scatterbug can eat poisonous leaves and roots.

Name: Spewpa
Pokedex Entry: If Rufflet attacks this Pokemon by pecking at it it will retaliate with its sharp fur and poisonous black powder.

Name: Vivillon
Pokedex Entry: The patterns on this Pokemon depend on the climate and topography of the land it was born in. This form is from lands where flowers bloom.

Name: Litleo
Pokedex Entry: When Litleo are young female Pyroar will teach them how to hunt. Once the Litleo mature they will leave the pride and set out on their own.

Name: Pyroar
Pokedex Entry: The females of a pride work together to bring down prey. It’s thanks to them that their pride doesn’t starve.

Name: Flabebe
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon can draw forth the power hidden within blooming wild flowers. It is particularly fond of red flowers.

Name: Floette
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon draws forth what power is left in withered flowers to make them healthy again. It holds a red flower.

Name: Florges
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon creates an impressive flower garden in its territory. It draws forth the power of the red flowers around its neck.

Name: Skiddo
Pokedex Entry: Until recently people living in the mountains would ride on the backs of these Pokemon to traverse the mountain paths.

Name: Gogoat
Pokedex Entry: It can sense the feelings of others by touching them with its horns. This species has assisted people with their work since 5000 years ago.

Name: Pancham
Pokedex Entry: It chooses a Pangoro as its master and then imitates its master’s actions. This is how it learns to battle and hunt for prey.

Name: Pangoro
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is quick to anger and it has no problem using its prodigious strength to get its way. It lives for duels against Obstagoon.

Name: Furfrou
Pokedex Entry: There was an era when aristocrats would compete to see who could trim their Furfrou’s fur into the most exquisite style.

Name: Espurr
Pokedex Entry: It keeps its ears covered to prevent the intense psychic power in its body from escaping but it falls unconscious if this power builds too much.

Name: Meowstic
Pokedex Entry: Though it has enough psychic power to blast away any opponent Meowstic prefers to support its allies rather than attack.

Name: Honedge
Pokedex Entry: Honedge’s soul once belonged to a person who was killed a long time ago by the sword that makes up Honedge’s body.

Name: Doublade
Pokedex Entry: Honedge evolves into twins. The two blades rub together to emit a metallic sound that unnerves opponents.

Name: Aegislash
Pokedex Entry: Generations of kings were attended by these Pokemon which used their spectral power to manipulate and control people and Pokemon.

Name: Spritzee
Pokedex Entry: A scent pouch within this Pokemon’s body allows it to create various scents. A change in its diet will alter the fragrance it produces.

Name: Aromatisse
Pokedex Entry: The scent that constantly emits from its fur is so powerful that this Pokemon’s companions will eventually lose their sense of smell.

Name: Swirlix
Pokedex Entry: It eats its own weight in sugar every day. If it doesn’t get enough sugar it becomes incredibly grumpy.

Name: Slurpuff
Pokedex Entry: By taking in a person’s scent it can sniff out their mental and physical condition. It’s hoped that this skill will have many medical applications.

Name: Inkay
Pokedex Entry: It protects itself from tough foes by flashing its luminescent spots to discourage them.

Name: Malamar
Pokedex Entry: Its hypnotic powers are dangerously strong. Anyone who falls under Malamar’s control loses their memories surrounding the event.

Name: Binacle
Pokedex Entry: After two Binacle find a suitably sized rock they adhere themselves to it and live together. They cooperate to gather food during high tide.

Name: Barbaracle
Pokedex Entry: Seven Binacle come together to form one Barbaracle. The Binacle that serves as the head gives orders to those serving as the limbs.

Name: Skrelp
Pokedex Entry: Skrelp evades its enemies by hiding amid drifting seaweed. It eats rotten seaweed to create its poison.

Name: Dragalge
Pokedex Entry: Using a liquid poison Dragalge indiscriminately attacks anything that wanders into its territory. This poison can corrode the undersides of boats.

Name: Clauncher
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon launches water by detonating gas inside its right claw. It snipes flying Pokemon.

Name: Clawitzer
Pokedex Entry: Clawitzer can move through the water at a speed of 60 knots by using gas inside its body to expel water from the back of its claw.

Name: Helioptile
Pokedex Entry: When spread the frills on its head act like solar panels generating the power behind this Pokemon’s electric moves.

Name: Heliolisk
Pokedex Entry: A now-vanished desert culture treasured these Pokemon. Appropriately when Heliolisk came to the Galar region treasure came with them.

Name: Tyrunt
Pokedex Entry: This is an ancient Pokemon revived in modern times. It has a violent disposition and it’ll tear apart anything it gets between its hefty jaws.

Name: Tyrantrum
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is from about 100000000 years ago. It has the presence of a king vicious but magnificent.

Name: Amaura
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon was successfully restored from a fossil. In the past it lived with others of its kind in cold lands where there were fewer predators.

Name: Aurorus
Pokedex Entry: Aurorus was restored from a fossil. It’s said that when this Pokemon howls auroras appear in the night sky.

Name: Sylveon
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon uses its ribbonlike feelers to send a soothing aura into its opponents erasing their hostility.

Name: Hawlucha
Pokedex Entry: Its elegant finishing moves—performed by nimbly leaping around using its wings—are polished in the forest where it was born and raised.

Name: Dedenne
Pokedex Entry: It’s small and its electricity-generating organ is not fully developed so it uses its tail to absorb electricity from people’s homes and charge itself.

Name: Carbink
Pokedex Entry: It has slept underground for hundreds of millions of years since its birth. It’s occasionally found during the excavation of caves.

Name: Goomy
Pokedex Entry: Most of a Goomy’s body is water. A membrane covers the whole Pokemon to prevent it from shriveling up in dry weather.

Name: Sliggoo
Pokedex Entry: The swirly protrusion on its back is filled with all its vital organs such as its brain and heart.

Name: Goodra
Pokedex Entry: It loves the rain. This mellow Pokemon can be seen walking around on the plains and in the mountains on rainy days.

Name: Klefki
Pokedex Entry: Once it absorbs a key’s metal ions it discards the key without a second thought. However it will hang on to keys it favors for decades.

Name: Phantump
Pokedex Entry: Legend tells that its green leaves can cure any illness. When plucked however the leaves will instantly wither away.

Name: Trevenant
Pokedex Entry: Using its roots Trevenant connects itself to trees and monitors every corner of its forest. It uses curses to drive intruders away.

Name: Pumpkaboo
Pokedex Entry: Spirits that wander this world are placed into Pumpkaboo’s body. They’re then moved on to the afterlife.

Name: Gourgeist
Pokedex Entry: Eerie cries emanate from its body in the dead of night. The sounds are said to be the wails of spirits who are suffering in the afterlife.

Name: Bergmite
Pokedex Entry: They live in mountainous regions of frigid cold. On rare occasions they ride on the back of an Avalugg to cross seas and move to new habitats.

Name: Avalugg
Pokedex Entry: As Avalugg walks along with Bergmite on its back it comes across pods of Cetitan. It lets them pass to avoid conflict.

Name: Noibat
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon emits ultrasonic waves from its large ears to search for fruit to eat. It mistakes Applin for its food.

Name: Noivern
Pokedex Entry: Ultrasonic waves emitted by a Noivern can pulverize a large boulder. This Pokemon has a cruel disposition.

Name: Xerneas
Pokedex Entry: Legends say it can share eternal life. It slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.

Name: Yveltal
Pokedex Entry: When this legendary Pokemon’s wings and tail feathers spread wide and glow red it absorbs the life force of living creatures.

Name: Zygarde
Pokedex Entry: This is Zygarde’s form when about half of its pieces have been assembled. It plays the role of monitoring the ecosystem.

Name: Diancie
Pokedex Entry: A sudden transformation of Carbink its pink glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.

Name: Hoopa
Pokedex Entry: In its true form it possesses a huge amount of power. Legends of its avarice tell how it once carried off an entire castle to gain the treasure hidden within.

Name: Volcanion
Pokedex Entry: It lets out billows of steam and disappears into the dense fog. It’s said to live in mountains where humans do not tread.

Name: Rowlet
Pokedex Entry: Silently it glides streaking toward its targets to get close to them. Before they even notice it it begins to pelt them with vicious kicks.

Name: Dartrix
Pokedex Entry: This narcissistic Pokemon is a clean freak. If you don’t groom it diligently it may stop listening to you.

Name: Decidueye
Pokedex Entry: It cunningly conceals arrow quills in its wings. It launches these quills with such precision that they can pierce a pebble at over a hundred yards.

Name: Litten
Pokedex Entry: If you try too hard to get close to it it won’t open up to you. Even if you do grow close giving it too much affection is still a no-no.

Name: Torracat
Pokedex Entry: At its throat it bears a bell of fire. The bell rings brightly whenever fire spews out.

Name: Incineroar
Pokedex Entry: When its fighting spirit is set alight the flames around its waist become especially intense.

Name: Popplio
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon can control balloons made of water. It practices diligently so it can learn to make big balloons.

Name: Brionne
Pokedex Entry: A skillful dancer it creates a sequence of water balloons as it dances then briskly bombards its enemies.

Name: Primarina
Pokedex Entry: To Primarina every battle is a stage. It takes down its prey with beautiful singing and dancing.

Name: Pikipek
Pokedex Entry: Using its beak to strike 16 times per second it opens holes in even the hardest of trees.

Name: Trumbeak
Pokedex Entry: It flies around using a hundred different cries in various ways to declare its territory to others.

Name: Toucannon
Pokedex Entry: The compressed gas in Toucannon’s beak launches seeds with such force that they can shatter large boulders.

Name: Yungoos
Pokedex Entry: Its stomach fills most of its torso. It wanders the same path every day searching for fresh food.

Name: Gumshoos
Pokedex Entry: Once it finds signs of prey it will patiently stake out the location waiting until the sun goes down.

Name: Grubbin
Pokedex Entry: Grubbin normally live underground but if they get unearthed by Hoothoot they may be found gathered around electric Pokemon.

Name: Charjabug
Pokedex Entry: Protected by a sturdy shell Charjabug eats large quantities of fresh and decomposing leaf litter in order to evolve.

Name: Vikavolt
Pokedex Entry: Displaying exceptional mobility it weaves between trees and shoots down bird Pokemon with its electromagnetic beams.

Name: Crabrawler
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon punches trees and eats the berries that drop down training itself and getting food at the same time.

Name: Crabominable
Pokedex Entry: The detached pincers of these Pokemon are delicious. Some Trainers bring Lechonk into the mountains just to search for them.

Name: Oricorio
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is incredibly popular possibly because its passionate dancing is a great match with the temperament of Paldean people.

Name: Cutiefly
Pokedex Entry: When it senses the auras of people or Pokemon who are having fun it will draw close and give them a painful poke with its long proboscis.

Name: Ribombee
Pokedex Entry: Ribombee can sense when people or Pokemon are feeling down and it will cheer them up with handmade pollen puffs.

Name: Rockruff
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is very friendly when it’s young. Its disposition becomes vicious once it matures but it never forgets the kindness of its master.

Name: Lycanroc
Pokedex Entry: Lycanroc attacks its prey with its sharp claws and fangs. It loyally obeys the instructions of a Trainer it trusts.

Name: Wishiwashi
Pokedex Entry: Individually they’re incredibly weak. It’s by gathering up into schools that they’re able to confront opponents.

Name: Mareanie
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon wanders the seaside looking for food. It often gets electric shocks from broken Pincurchin spines that it tries to eat.

Name: Toxapex
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon lives within a dome made by its own legs. Toxapex monitors its surroundings by sensing the flow of the tide through its spikes.

Name: Mudbray
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon covers itself in mud that it has regurgitated. The mud won’t dry out even if it’s exposed to the sun for a long time.

Name: Mudsdale
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon has been treasured not just for its physical labor but also because it produces high-quality mud used for making pottery.

Name: Dewpider
Pokedex Entry: Dewpider uses sticky threads to create the water bubble that covers its head so the bubble very rarely bursts.

Name: Araquanid
Pokedex Entry: A caring Pokemon Araquanid carries Dewpider around inside its water bubble to protect them as it walks. It protects its food in its bubble too.

Name: Fomantis
Pokedex Entry: Fomantis hates having its naps interrupted. It fires off beams using energy it gathers by bathing in the sun.

Name: Lurantis
Pokedex Entry: By masquerading as a bug Pokemon it lowers the guard of actual bug Pokemon lured in by a scent of sweet flowers. Its sickles bring them down.

Name: Morelull
Pokedex Entry: Pokemon living in the forest eat the delicious caps on Morelull’s head. The caps regrow overnight.

Name: Shiinotic
Pokedex Entry: Its flickering spores lure in prey and put them to sleep. Once this Pokemon has its prey snoozing it drains their vitality with its fingertips.

Name: Salandit
Pokedex Entry: It taunts its prey and lures them into narrow rocky areas where it then sprays them with toxic gas to make them dizzy and take them down.

Name: Salazzle
Pokedex Entry: Salazzle makes its opponents light-headed with poisonous gas then captivates them with alluring movements to turn them into loyal servants.

Name: Stufful
Pokedex Entry: Its fluffy fur is a delight to pet but carelessly reaching out to touch this Pokemon could result in painful retaliation.

Name: Bewear
Pokedex Entry: Once it accepts you as a friend it tries to show its affection with a hug. Letting it do that is dangerous—it could easily shatter your bones.

Name: Bounsweet
Pokedex Entry: Its sweat is sweet like syrup made from boiled-down fruit. Because of this Bounsweet was highly valued in the past when sweeteners were scarce.

Name: Steenee
Pokedex Entry: Steenee spreads a sweet scent that makes others feel invigorated. This same scent is popular for antiperspirants.

Name: Tsareena
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is proud and aggressive. However it is said that a Tsareena will instantly become calm if someone touches the crown on its calyx.

Name: Comfey
Pokedex Entry: It uses its vine to pick flowers. The flowers that Comfey attaches to itself develop healing properties.

Name: Oranguru
Pokedex Entry: People used to mistake Oranguru for a human when they saw it issue command after command to the other Pokemon of the forest.

Name: Passimian
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon battles by throwing hard berries. It won’t obey a Trainer who throws Poke Balls without skill.

Name: Wimpod
Pokedex Entry: It’s nature’s cleaner—it eats anything and everything including garbage and rotten things. The ground near its nest is always clean.

Name: Golisopod
Pokedex Entry: It will do anything to win taking advantage of every opening and finishing opponents off with the small claws on its front legs.

Name: Sandygast
Pokedex Entry: If it loses its shovel it will stick something else—like a branch—in its head to make do until it finds another shovel.

Name: Palossand
Pokedex Entry: The terrifying Palossand drags smaller Pokemon into its sandy body. Once its victims are trapped it drains them of their vitality whenever it pleases.

Name: Pyukumuku
Pokedex Entry: It lives in warm shallow waters. If it encounters a foe it will spit out its internal organs as a means to punch them.

Name: Type: Null
Pokedex Entry: Rumor has it that the theft of top-secret research notes led to a new instance of this Pokemon being created in the Galar region.

Name: Silvally
Pokedex Entry: A solid bond of trust between this Pokemon and its Trainer awakened the strength hidden within Silvally. It can change its type at will.

Name: Minior
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is born in the ozone layer. It falls to the ground once the outer shell enclosing its core grows heavy.

Name: Komala
Pokedex Entry: Komala spends its entire life sleeping. It feeds on leaves that contain a potent poison only Komala can break down.

Name: Turtonator
Pokedex Entry: Explosive substances coat the shell on its back. Enemies that dare attack it will be blown away by an immense detonation.

Name: Togedemaru
Pokedex Entry: With the long hairs on its back this Pokemon takes in electricity from other electric Pokemon. It stores what it absorbs in an electric sac.

Name: Mimikyu
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon lives in dark places untouched by sunlight. When it appears before humans it hides itself under a cloth that resembles a Pikachu.

Name: Bruxish
Pokedex Entry: It grinds its teeth with great force to stimulate its brain. It fires the psychic energy created by this process from the protuberance on its head.

Name: Drampa
Pokedex Entry: The mountains it calls home are nearly two miles in height. On rare occasions it descends to play with the children living in the towns below.

Name: Dhelmise
Pokedex Entry: After a piece of seaweed merged with debris from a sunken ship it was reborn as this ghost Pokemon.

Name: Jangmo-o
Pokedex Entry: The scale atop its head is useful for both offense and defense. It bravely stands and faces its foes rather than turning tail even if its foes are strong.

Name: Hakamo-o
Pokedex Entry: It gets into fistfights so intense that the scales on its arms peel off. Bare arms are a sign of valiance.

Name: Kommo-o
Pokedex Entry: It lets its arm hang and then—quick as a flash—swings upward to land its specialty punch and send the opponent flying high into the sky.

Name: Tapu Koko
Pokedex Entry: Although it’s called a guardian deity if a person or Pokemon puts it in a bad mood it will become a malevolent deity and attack.

Name: Tapu Lele
Pokedex Entry: It heals the wounds of people and Pokemon by sprinkling them with its sparkling scales. This guardian deity is worshiped on Akala.

Name: Tapu Bulu
Pokedex Entry: Although it’s called a guardian deity it’s violent enough to crush anyone it sees as an enemy.

Name: Tapu Fini
Pokedex Entry: This guardian deity of Poni Island manipulates water. Because it lives deep within a thick fog it came to be both feared and revered.

Name: Cosmog
Pokedex Entry: Even though its helpless gaseous body can be blown away by the slightest breeze it doesn’t seem to care.

Name: Cosmoem
Pokedex Entry: The king who ruled Alola in times of antiquity called it the “cocoon of the stars” and built an altar to worship it.

Name: Solgaleo
Pokedex Entry: Sometimes the result of its opening an Ultra Wormhole is that energy and life-forms from other worlds are called here to this world.

Name: Lunala
Pokedex Entry: Records of it exist in writings from long long ago where it was known by the name “the beast that calls the moon.”

Name: Nihilego
Pokedex Entry: A life-form from another world it was dubbed a UB and is thought to produce a strong neurotoxin.

Name: Buzzwole
Pokedex Entry: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

Name: Pheromosa
Pokedex Entry: A life-form that lives in another world its body is thin and supple but it also possesses great power.

Name: Xurkitree
Pokedex Entry: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

Name: Celesteela
Pokedex Entry: One of the dangerous UBs high energy readings can be detected coming from both of its huge arms.

Name: Kartana
Pokedex Entry: This Ultra Beast’s body which is as thin as paper is like a sharpened sword.

Name: Guzzlord
Pokedex Entry: Although it’s alien to this world and a danger here it’s apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

Name: Necrozma
Pokedex Entry: It looks somehow pained as it rages around in search of light which serves as its energy. It’s apparently from another world.

Name: Magearna
Pokedex Entry: It synchronizes its consciousness with others to understand their feelings. This faculty makes it useful for taking care of people.

Name: Marshadow
Pokedex Entry: It slips into the shadows of others and mimics their powers and movements. As it improves it becomes stronger than those it’s imitating.

Name: Poipole
Pokedex Entry: This Ultra Beast is well enough liked to be chosen as a first partner in its own world.

Name: Naganadel
Pokedex Entry: It stores hundreds of liters of poisonous liquid inside its body. It is one of the organisms known as UBs.

Name: Stakataka
Pokedex Entry: It appeared from an Ultra Wormhole. Each one appears to be made up of many life-forms stacked one on top of each other.

Name: Blacephalon
Pokedex Entry: It slithers toward people. Then without warning it triggers the explosion of its own head. It’s apparently one kind of Ultra Beast.

Name: Zeraora
Pokedex Entry: It electrifies its claws and tears its opponents apart with them. Even if they dodge its attack they’ll be electrocuted by the flying sparks.

Name: Meltan
Pokedex Entry: It melts particles of iron and other metals found in the subsoil so it can absorb them into its body of molten steel.

Name: Melmetal
Pokedex Entry: At the end of its life-span Melmetal will rust and fall apart. The small shards left behind will eventually be reborn as Meltan.

Name: Grookey
Pokedex Entry: The stick Grookey holds has grown harder and more flexible after soaking in the energy that emanates from inside Grookey’s body.

Name: Thwackey
Pokedex Entry: It skillfully uses its two sticks not only for drumming out rapid beats but also for pummeling opponents during battle.

Name: Rillaboom
Pokedex Entry: Though it has a calm disposition it won’t tolerate those who drum up discord. It strictly disciplines offenders until they learn their lesson.

Name: Scorbunny
Pokedex Entry: Once its body has heated up Scorbunny can use the full extent of its power. That’s why it does warm-up exercises.

Name: Raboot
Pokedex Entry: Thanks to its soft and fluffy fur Raboot can easily heat up its fire energy and produce flames with more power.

Name: Cinderace
Pokedex Entry: Although Cinderace loses its cool easily it will battle flawlessly for a Trainer it trusts.

Name: Sobble
Pokedex Entry: It gets berries to eat by shooting them down with bullets of water it spurts from its mouth. Its aim is perfect.

Name: Drizzile
Pokedex Entry: It extends its long slimy tongue at blinding speeds and finishes off its prey with great skill.

Name: Inteleon
Pokedex Entry: It uses special lenses in its eyes to sense things about its opponents—like their body heat—then attacks once it identifies a weak spot.

Name: Skwovet
Pokedex Entry: It stores berries in its cheeks. When there are no berries to be found Skwovet will stuff pebbles into its cheeks to stave off its cravings.

Name: Greedent
Pokedex Entry: If it spots a berry tree it will immediately go to gather berries without a sideways glance—even if it’s in the middle of a battle.

Name: Rookidee
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is brave and reckless. The white markings around a Rookidee’s eyes intimidate fainthearted Pokemon.

Name: Corvisquire
Pokedex Entry: It’s said that the reason behind Corvisquire’s high level of intelligence is the large size of its brain relative to those of other bird Pokemon.

Name: Corviknight
Pokedex Entry: Corviknight can’t serve as a taxi service in Paldea because the Pokemon’s natural predators will attack it while it flies endangering the customer.

Name: Blipbug
Pokedex Entry: A constant collector of information this Pokemon is very smart. Very strong is what it isn’t.

Name: Dottler
Pokedex Entry: It barely moves but it’s still alive. Hiding in its shell without food or water seems to have awakened its psychic powers.

Name: Orbeetle
Pokedex Entry: It’s famous for its high level of intelligence and the large size of its brain is proof that it also possesses immense psychic power.

Name: Nickit
Pokedex Entry: Aided by the soft pads on its feet it silently raids the food stores of other Pokemon. It survives off its ill-gotten gains.

Name: Thievul
Pokedex Entry: It secretly marks potential targets with a scent. By following the scent it stalks its targets and steals from them when they least expect it.

Name: Gossifleur
Pokedex Entry: It anchors itself in the ground with its single leg then basks in the sun. After absorbing enough sunlight its petals spread as it blooms brilliantly.

Name: Eldegoss
Pokedex Entry: The seeds attached to its cotton fluff are full of nutrients. It spreads them on the wind so that plants and other Pokemon can benefit from them.

Name: Wooloo
Pokedex Entry: Its curly fleece is such an effective cushion that this Pokemon could fall off a cliff and stand right back up at the bottom unharmed.

Name: Dubwool
Pokedex Entry: Weave a carpet from its springy wool and you end up with something closer to a trampoline. You’ll start to bounce the moment you set foot on it.

Name: Chewtle
Pokedex Entry: Its large front tooth is still growing in. When the tooth itches this Pokemon will bite another Chewtle’s horn and the two Pokemon will tussle.

Name: Drednaw
Pokedex Entry: Its massive jagged teeth can crush a boulder in a single bite. This Pokemon has an extremely vicious disposition.

Name: Yamper
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is very popular as a herding dog in the Galar region. As it runs it generates electricity from the base of its tail.

Name: Boltund
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon generates electricity and channels it into its legs to keep them going strong. Boltund can run nonstop for three full days.

Name: Rolycoly
Pokedex Entry: On sunny days Rolycoly will come out onto grassy plains and roll around. Then it will eat the grass that gets tangled in its wheel-like leg.

Name: Carkol
Pokedex Entry: The temperature inside its body increases when it experiences strong emotions. It rolls around frantically while spewing flames.

Name: Coalossal
Pokedex Entry: To intimidate its opponents Coalossal will vigorously shake its body scattering coal from its smoldering back.

Name: Applin
Pokedex Entry: It grows by eating the flesh of an apple. Applin uses its own body fluid to strengthen the apple’s skin and prevent it from rotting.

Name: Flapple
Pokedex Entry: It flutters around while seeking an opening in the opponent’s guard then attacks by spitting acidic liquid strong enough to melt metal.

Name: Appletun
Pokedex Entry: It feeds mainly on sweet apples. It will also eat small bug Pokemon that are attracted by its sweet nectar.

Name: Silicobra
Pokedex Entry: Silicobra’s neck pouch which can inflate and deflate like a balloon gets more elastic each time Silicobra sheds its skin.

Name: Sandaconda
Pokedex Entry: It will expand its body as much as it can and then contract itself blasting out sand with enough force to wash away a dump truck.

Name: Cramorant
Pokedex Entry: Cramorant instinctively swallow everything whole. They’re at their most formidable when they’re struggling to swallow overly large prey.

Name: Arrokuda
Pokedex Entry: Arrokuda can swim quickly only in a straight line. The ones that become sluggish from overeating are the first to be targeted by flocks of Wattrel.

Name: Barraskewda
Pokedex Entry: It spins its tail fins to leap from the water then viciously bites down on Wingull flying close to the water’s surface.

Name: Toxel
Pokedex Entry: It has no problem drinking dirty water. An organ inside Toxel’s body filters such water into a poisonous liquid that is harmless to Toxel.

Name: Toxtricity
Pokedex Entry: Many youths admire the way this Pokemon listlessly picks fights and keeps its cool no matter what opponent it faces.

Name: Sizzlipede
Pokedex Entry: It stores flammable gas in its body and uses it to generate heat. The yellow sections on its belly get particularly hot.

Name: Centiskorch
Pokedex Entry: When it heats up its body temperature reaches about 1500 degrees Fahrenheit. It lashes its body like a whip and launches itself at enemies.

Name: Clobbopus
Pokedex Entry: It’s very curious but its means of investigating things is to try to punch them with its tentacles. The search for food is what brings it onto land.

Name: Grapploct
Pokedex Entry: A body made up of nothing but muscle makes the grappling moves this Pokemon performs with its tentacles tremendously powerful.

Name: Sinistea
Pokedex Entry: The soul of someone who died alone possessed some leftover tea. This Pokemon appears in hotels and houses.

Name: Polteageist
Pokedex Entry: The tea that composes Polteageist’s body has a distinct and enjoyable flavor. Drinking too much however can be fatal.

Name: Hatenna
Pokedex Entry: Because the emotions of others constantly flow into its head this Pokemon prefers environments where no other creatures live.

Name: Hattrem
Pokedex Entry: To this Pokemon strong emotions apparently feel like incredibly loud noises—even if the emotions are happy ones.

Name: Hatterene
Pokedex Entry: Hatterene knocks out those that intrude in its home forest by blasting them with a beam then slashing with claws enhanced by psychic power.

Name: Impidimp
Pokedex Entry: The reason this Pokemon causes trouble for those it feels close to is because Impidimp itself gets irritable if it can’t absorb negative emotions.

Name: Morgrem
Pokedex Entry: Morgrem prefers dirty tactics like ambushing because it doesn’t have confidence in its brawn.

Name: Grimmsnarl
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon has complete control over its hair. Grimmsnarl normally keeps its hair wrapped around its body to support its muscles.

Name: Obstagoon
Pokedex Entry: Its voice is staggering in volume. Obstagoon has a tendency to take on a threatening posture and shout—this move is known as Obstruct.

Name: Perrserker
Pokedex Entry: What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokemon lives for the thrill of battle.

Name: Cursola
Pokedex Entry: Its shell is overflowing with its heightened otherworldly energy. The ectoplasm serves as protection for this Pokemon’s core spirit.

Name: Sirfetch'd
Pokedex Entry: Only Farfetch’d that have survived many battles can attain this evolution. When this Pokemon’s leek withers it will retire from combat.

Name: Mr. Rime
Pokedex Entry: It’s highly skilled at tap-dancing. It waves its cane of ice in time with its graceful movements.

Name: Runerigus
Pokedex Entry: A powerful curse was woven into an ancient painting. After absorbing the spirit of a Yamask the painting began to move.

Name: Milcery
Pokedex Entry: The more sweet aromas it absorbs the more its body swells. Milcery will deflate when its energy level drops.

Name: Alcremie
Pokedex Entry: Desserts that Alcremie have decorated with their cream have a rich sweet flavor and bring happiness to all who eat them.

Name: Falinks
Pokedex Entry: The brass which is the one that stands at the front and issues orders is the strongest and smartest of the six.

Name: Pincurchin
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon generates electricity when it digests food. It uses its five hard teeth to scrape seaweed off surfaces and eat it.

Name: Snom
Pokedex Entry: It eats snow that has accumulated on the ground. It prefers soft freshly fallen snow so it will eat its way up a mountain aiming for the peak.

Name: Frosmoth
Pokedex Entry: Frosmoth senses air currents with its antennae. It sends its scales drifting on frigid air making them fall like snow.

Name: Stonjourner
Pokedex Entry: The elemental composition of the rocks that form its body were found to match the bedrock of a land far away from this Pokemon’s habitat.

Name: Eiscue
Pokedex Entry: On hot days these Pokemon press their ice cube heads together and pass the time cooling each other down.

Name: Indeedee
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon picks up on the positive emotions of other creatures via its horns and uses those emotions to fuel itself.

Name: Morpeko
Pokedex Entry: Morpeko eats seeds constantly to keep its hunger at bay. If it’s hungry for too long it grows wild and brutish.

Name: Cufant
Pokedex Entry: Using the pointy tip of its trunk it carves off chunks of hard rocks to eat. It is very docile and helps people with physical labor.

Name: Copperajah
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon was brought to Paldea long ago by people from a faraway land. It’s so strong that it can easily pull an airplane.

Name: Dracozolt
Pokedex Entry: In ancient times it was unbeatable thanks to its powerful lower body but it went extinct anyway after it depleted all its plant-based food sources.

Name: Arctozolt
Pokedex Entry: The shaking of its freezing upper half is what generates its electricity. It has a hard time walking around.

Name: Dracovish
Pokedex Entry: Powerful legs and jaws made it the apex predator of its time. Its own overhunting of its prey was what drove it to extinction.

Name: Arctovish
Pokedex Entry: Though it’s able to capture prey by freezing its surroundings it has trouble eating the prey afterward because its mouth is on top of its head.

Name: Duraludon
Pokedex Entry: Duraludon’s body is comprised of a special metal that’s lightweight and scratch resistant. It’s also smooth as though it was given a mirror finish.

Name: Dreepy
Pokedex Entry: In the evening groups of Dreepy will fly at high speeds over the ocean and poke at Pokemon in the water for fun.

Name: Drakloak
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon flies around at over 120 miles per hour. If a Drakloak is defeated in a battle its Dreepy will wander off without a second thought.

Name: Dragapult
Pokedex Entry: Dragapult can make its whole body transparent by clearing its mind and focusing. Even the Dreepy in Dragapult’s horns become invisible.

Name: Zacian
Pokedex Entry: Known as a legendary hero this Pokemon absorbs metal particles transforming them into a weapon it uses to battle.

Name: Zamazenta
Pokedex Entry: In times past it worked together with a king of the people to save the Galar region. It absorbs metal that it then uses in battle.

Name: Eternatus
Pokedex Entry: The core on its chest absorbs energy emanating from the lands of the Galar region. This energy is what allows Eternatus to stay active.

Name: Kubfu
Pokedex Entry: Kubfu trains hard to perfect its moves. The moves it masters will determine which form it takes when it evolves.

Name: Urshifu
Pokedex Entry: This form of Urshifu is a strong believer in the one-hit KO. Its strategy is to leap in close to foes and land a devastating blow with a hardened fist.

Name: Zarude
Pokedex Entry: Within dense forests this Pokemon lives in a pack with others of its kind. It’s incredibly aggressive and the other Pokemon of the forest fear it.

Name: Regieleki
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is a cluster of electrical energy. It’s said that removing the rings on Regieleki’s body will unleash the Pokemon’s latent power.

Name: Regidrago
Pokedex Entry: An academic theory proposes that Regidrago’s arms were once the head of an ancient dragon Pokemon. The theory remains unproven.

Name: Glastrier
Pokedex Entry: Glastrier emits intense cold from its hooves. It’s also a belligerent Pokemon—anything it wants it takes by force.

Name: Spectrier
Pokedex Entry: It probes its surroundings with all its senses save one—it doesn’t use its sense of sight. Spectrier’s kicks are said to separate soul from body.

Name: Calyrex
Pokedex Entry: Calyrex is a merciful Pokemon capable of providing healing and blessings. It reigned over the Galar region in times of yore.

Name: Wyrdeer
Pokedex Entry: The black orbs shine with an uncanny light when the Pokemon is erecting invisible barriers. The fur shed from its beard retains heat well and is a highly useful material for winter clothing.

Name: Kleavor
Pokedex Entry: Parts of its body turned to stone when it evolved thanks to an extremely rare ore found in volcanic areas.

Name: Ursaluna
Pokedex Entry: I believe it was Hisui’s swampy terrain that gave Ursaluna its burly physique and newfound capacity to manipulate peat at will.

Name: Basculegion
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is cloaked in the souls of its comrades who perished during a punishing journey to the river of their birth.

Name: Sneasler
Pokedex Entry: Because of Sneasler’s virulent poison and daunting physical prowess no other species could hope to best it on the frozen highlands. Preferring solitude this species does not form packs.

Name: Overqwil
Pokedex Entry: Overqwil’s poisonous spikes will reflexively react even while Overqwil sleeps stabbing any moving thing that approaches.

Name: Enamorus
Pokedex Entry: When it flies to this land from across the sea the bitter winter comes to an end. According to legend this Pokemon’s love gives rise to the budding of fresh life across Hisui.

Name: Sprigatito
Pokedex Entry: Its fluffy fur is similar in composition to plants. This Pokemon frequently washes its face to keep it from drying out.

Name: Floragato
Pokedex Entry: Floragato deftly wields the vine hidden beneath its long fur slamming the hard flower bud against its opponents.

Name: Meowscarada
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon uses the reflective fur lining its cape to camouflage the stem of its flower creating the illusion that the flower is floating.

Name: Fuecoco
Pokedex Entry: It lies on warm rocks and uses the heat absorbed by its square-shaped scales to create fire energy.

Name: Crocalor
Pokedex Entry: The combination of Crocalor’s fire energy and overflowing vitality has caused an egg-shaped fireball to appear on the Pokemon’s head.

Name: Skeledirge
Pokedex Entry: The fiery bird changes shape when Skeledirge sings. Rumor has it that the bird was born when the fireball on Skeledirge’s head gained a soul.

Name: Quaxly
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon migrated to Paldea from distant lands long ago. The gel secreted by its feathers repels water and grime.

Name: Quaxwell
Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon constantly run through shallow waters to train their legs then compete with each other to see which of them kicks most gracefully.

Name: Quaquaval
Pokedex Entry: A single kick from a Quaquaval can send a truck rolling. This Pokemon uses its powerful legs to perform striking dances from far-off lands.

Name: Lechonk
Pokedex Entry: It searches for food all day. It possesses a keen sense of smell but doesn’t use it for anything other than foraging.

Name: Oinkologne
Pokedex Entry: Oinkologne is proud of its fine glossy skin. It emits a concentrated scent from the tip of its tail.

Name: Tarountula
Pokedex Entry: The ball of threads wrapped around its body is elastic enough to deflect the scythes of Scyther this Pokemon’s natural enemy.

Name: Spidops
Pokedex Entry: It clings to branches and ceilings using its threads and moves without a sound. It takes out its prey before the prey even notices it.

Name: Nymble
Pokedex Entry: It has its third set of legs folded up. When it’s in a tough spot this Pokemon jumps over 30 feet using the strength of its legs.

Name: Lokix
Pokedex Entry: When it decides to fight all out it stands on its previously folded legs to enter Showdown Mode. It neutralizes its enemies in short order.

Name: Pawmi
Pokedex Entry: It has underdeveloped electric sacs on its cheeks. These sacs can produce electricity only if Pawmi rubs them furiously with the pads on its forepaws.

Name: Pawmo
Pokedex Entry: When its group is attacked Pawmo is the first to leap into battle defeating enemies with a fighting technique that utilizes electric shocks.

Name: Pawmot
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon normally is slow to react but once it enters battle it will strike down its enemies with lightning-fast movements.

Name: Tandemaus
Pokedex Entry: Exhibiting great teamwork they use their incisors to cut pieces out of any material that might be useful for a nest then make off with them.

Name: Maushold
Pokedex Entry: The two little ones just appeared one day. The group might be a family of related Pokemon but nobody knows for sure.

Name: Fidough
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is smooth and moist to the touch. Yeast in Fidough’s breath induces fermentation in the Pokemon’s vicinity.

Name: Dachsbun
Pokedex Entry: The pleasant aroma that emanates from this Pokemon’s body helps wheat grow so Dachsbun has been treasured by farming villages.

Name: Smoliv
Pokedex Entry: It protects itself from enemies by emitting oil from the fruit on its head. This oil is bitter and astringent enough to make someone flinch.

Name: Dolliv
Pokedex Entry: Dolliv shares its tasty fresh-scented oil with others. This species has coexisted with humans since times long gone.

Name: Arboliva
Pokedex Entry: This calm Pokemon is very compassionate. It will share its delicious nutrient-rich oil with weakened Pokemon.

Name: Squawkabilly
Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon prefer to live in cities. They form flocks based on the color of their feathers and they fight over territory.

Name: Nacli
Pokedex Entry: It was born in a layer of rock salt deep under the earth. This species was particularly treasured in the old days as they would share precious salt.

Name: Naclstack
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon dry cures its prey by spraying salt over them. The curing process steals away the water in the prey’s body.

Name: Garganacl
Pokedex Entry: Garganacl will rub its fingertips together and sprinkle injured Pokemon with salt. Even severe wounds will promptly heal afterward.

Name: Charcadet
Pokedex Entry: Burnt charcoal came to life and became a Pokemon. Possessing a fiery fighting spirit Charcadet will battle even tough opponents.

Name: Armarouge
Pokedex Entry: Armarouge evolved through the use of a set of armor that belonged to a distinguished warrior. This Pokemon is incredibly loyal.

Name: Ceruledge
Pokedex Entry: Armarouge evolved through the use of a set of armor that belonged to a distinguished warrior. This Pokemon is incredibly loyal.

Name: Tadbulb
Pokedex Entry: Tadbulb shakes its tail to generate electricity. If it senses danger it will make its head blink on and off to alert its allies.

Name: Bellibolt
Pokedex Entry: When this Pokemon expands and contracts its wobbly body the belly-button dynamo in its stomach produces a huge amount of electricity.

Name: Wattrel
Pokedex Entry: When its wings catch the wind the bones within produce electricity. This Pokemon dives into the ocean catching prey by electrocuting them.

Name: Kilowattrel
Pokedex Entry: Kilowattrel inflates its throat sac to amplify its electricity. By riding the wind this Pokemon can fly over 430 miles in a day.

Name: Maschiff
Pokedex Entry: It always scowls in an attempt to make opponents take it seriously but even crying children will burst into laughter when they see Maschiff’s face.

Name: Mabosstiff
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon can store energy in its large dewlap. Mabosstiff unleashes this energy all at once to blow away enemies.

Name: Shroodle
Pokedex Entry: Though usually a mellow Pokemon it will sink its sharp poison-soaked front teeth into any that anger it causing paralysis in the object of its ire.

Name: Grafaiai
Pokedex Entry: The color of the poisonous saliva depends on what the Pokemon eats. Grafaiai covers its fingers in its saliva and draws patterns on trees in forests.

Name: Bramblin
Pokedex Entry: A soul unable to move on to the afterlife was blown around by the wind until it got tangled up with dried grass and became a Pokemon.

Name: Brambleghast
Pokedex Entry: It will open the branches of its head to envelop its prey. Once it absorbs all the life energy it needs it expels the prey and discards it.

Name: Toedscool
Pokedex Entry: Toedscool lives in muggy forests. The flaps that fall from its body are chewy and very delicious.

Name: Toedscruel
Pokedex Entry: These Pokemon gather into groups and form colonies deep within forests. They absolutely hate it when strangers approach.

Name: Klawf
Pokedex Entry: Klawf hangs upside-down from cliffs waiting for prey. But Klawf can’t remain in this position for long because its blood rushes to its head.

Name: Capsakid
Pokedex Entry: The more sunlight this Pokemon bathes in the more spicy chemicals are produced by its body and thus the spicier its moves become.

Name: Scovillain
Pokedex Entry: The red head converts spicy chemicals into fire energy and blasts the surrounding area with a super spicy stream of flame.

Name: Rellor
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon creates a mud ball by mixing sand and dirt with psychic energy. It treasures its mud ball more than its own life.

Name: Rabsca
Pokedex Entry: The body that supports the ball barely moves. Therefore it is thought that the true body of this Pokemon is actually inside the ball.

Name: Flittle
Pokedex Entry: Flittle’s toes levitate about half an inch above the ground because of the psychic power emitted from the frills on the Pokemon’s belly.

Name: Espathra
Pokedex Entry: It immobilizes opponents by bathing them in psychic power from its large eyes. Despite its appearance it has a vicious temperament.

Name: Tinkatink
Pokedex Entry: It swings its handmade hammer around to protect itself but the hammer is often stolen by Pokemon that eat metal.

Name: Tinkatuff
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon will attack groups of Pawniard and Bisharp gathering metal from them in order to create a large and sturdy hammer.

Name: Tinkaton
Pokedex Entry: This intelligent Pokemon has a very daring disposition. It knocks rocks into the sky with its hammer aiming for flying Corviknight.

Name: Wiglett
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon can pick up the scent of a Veluza just over 65 feet away and will hide itself in the sand.

Name: Wugtrio
Pokedex Entry: It has a vicious temperament contrary to what its appearance may suggest. It wraps its long bodies around prey then drags the prey into its den.

Name: Bombirdier
Pokedex Entry: It gathers things up in an apron made from shed feathers added to the Pokemon’s chest feathers then drops those things from high places for fun.

Name: Finizen
Pokedex Entry: It likes playing with others of its kind using the water ring on its tail. It uses ultrasonic waves to sense the emotions of other living creatures.

Name: Palafin
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon changes its appearance if it hears its allies calling for help. Palafin will never show anybody its moment of transformation.

Name: Varoom
Pokedex Entry: It is said that this Pokemon was born when an unknown poison Pokemon entered and inspirited an engine left at a scrap-processing factory.

Name: Revavroom
Pokedex Entry: It creates a gas out of poison and minerals from rocks. It then detonates the gas in its cylinders—now numbering eight—to generate energy.

Name: Cyclizar
Pokedex Entry: Apparently Cyclizar has been allowing people to ride on its back since ancient times. Depictions of this have been found in 10000-year-old murals.

Name: Orthworm
Pokedex Entry: When attacked this Pokemon will wield the tendrils on its body like fists and pelt the opponent with a storm of punches.

Name: Glimmet
Pokedex Entry: It absorbs nutrients from cave walls. The petals it wears are made of crystallized poison.

Name: Glimmora
Pokedex Entry: When this Pokemon detects danger it will open up its crystalline petals and fire beams from its conical body.

Name: Greavard
Pokedex Entry: It is said that a dog Pokemon that died in the wild without ever interacting with a human was reborn as this Pokemon.

Name: Houndstone
Pokedex Entry: Houndstone spends most of its time sleeping in graveyards. Among all the dog Pokemon this one is most loyal to its master.

Name: Flamigo
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon apparently ties the base of its neck into a knot so that energy stored in its belly does not escape from its beak.

Name: Cetoddle
Pokedex Entry: This species left the ocean and began living on land a very long time ago. It seems to be closely related to Wailmer.

Name: Cetitan
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon wanders around snowy icy areas. It protects its body with powerful muscles and a thick layer of fat under its skin.

Name: Veluza
Pokedex Entry: When Veluza discards unnecessary flesh its mind becomes honed and its psychic power increases. The spare flesh has a mild but delicious flavor.

Name: Dondozo
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon is a glutton but it’s bad at getting food. It teams up with a Tatsugiri to catch prey.

Name: Tatsugiri
Pokedex Entry: This is a small dragon Pokemon. It lives inside the mouth of Dondozo to protect itself from enemies on the outside.

Name: Annihilape
Pokedex Entry: When its anger rose beyond a critical point this Pokemon gained power that is unfettered by the limits of its physical body.

Name: Clodsire
Pokedex Entry: When attacked this Pokemon will retaliate by sticking thick spines out from its body. It’s a risky move that puts everything on the line.

Name: Farigiraf
Pokedex Entry: Now that the brain waves from the head and tail are synced up the psychic power of this Pokemon is 10 times stronger than Girafarig’s.

Name: Dudunsparce
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon uses its hard tail to make its nest by boring holes into bedrock deep underground. The nest can reach lengths of over six miles.

Name: Kingambit
Pokedex Entry: Only a Bisharp that stands above all others in its vast army can evolve into Kingambit.

Name: Great Tusk
Pokedex Entry: Sightings of this Pokemon have occurred in recent years. The name Great Tusk was taken from a creature listed in a certain book.

Name: Scream Tail
Pokedex Entry: There has been only one reported sighting of this Pokemon. It resembles a mysterious creature depicted in an old expedition journal.

Name: Brute Bonnet
Pokedex Entry: It is possible that the creature listed as Brute Bonnet in a certain book could actually be this Pokemon.

Name: Flutter Mane
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon has characteristics similar to those of Flutter Mane a creature mentioned in a certain book.

Name: Slither Wing
Pokedex Entry: This mysterious Pokemon has some similarities to a creature that an old book introduced as Slither Wing.

Name: Sandy Shocks
Pokedex Entry: No records exist of this Pokemon being caught. Data is lacking but the Pokemon’s traits match up with a creature shown in an expedition journal.

Name: Iron Treads
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon closely resembles a scientific weapon that a paranormal magazine claimed was sent to this planet by aliens.

Name: Iron Bundle
Pokedex Entry: Its shape is similar to a robot featured in a paranormal magazine article. The robot was said to have been created by an ancient civilization.

Name: Iron Hands
Pokedex Entry: It is very similar to a cyborg covered exclusively by a paranormal magazine. The cyborg was said to be the modified form of a certain athlete.

Name: Iron Jugulis
Pokedex Entry: It resembles a certain Pokemon introduced in a paranormal magazine described as the offspring of a Hydreigon that fell in love with a robot.

Name: Iron Moth
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon resembles an unknown object described in a paranormal magazine as a UFO sent to observe humanity.

Name: Iron Thorns
Pokedex Entry: It has some similarities to a Pokemon introduced in a dubious magazine as a Tyranitar from one billion years into the future.

Name: Frigibax
Pokedex Entry: Frigibax absorbs heat through its dorsal fin and converts the heat into ice energy. The higher the temperature the more energy Frigibax stores.

Name: Arctibax
Pokedex Entry: Arctibax freezes the air around it protecting its face with an ice mask and turning its dorsal fin into a blade of ice.

Name: Baxcalibur
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon blasts cryogenic air out from its mouth. This air can instantly freeze even liquid-hot lava.

Name: Gimmighoul
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon was born inside a treasure chest about 1500 years ago. It sucks the life-force out of scoundrels who try to steal the treasure.

Name: Gholdengo
Pokedex Entry: Its body seems to be made up of 1000 coins. This Pokemon gets along well with others and is quick to make friends with anybody.

Name: Wo-Chien
Pokedex Entry: The grudge of a person punished for writing the king’s evil deeds upon wooden tablets has clad itself in dead leaves to become a Pokemon.

Name: Chien-Pao
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon can control 100 tons of fallen snow. It plays around innocently by leaping in and out of avalanches it has caused.

Name: Ting-Lu
Pokedex Entry: The fear poured into an ancient ritual vessel has clad itself in rocks and dirt to become a Pokemon.

Name: Chi-Yu
Pokedex Entry: It controls flames burning at over 5400 degrees Fahrenheit. It casually swims through the sea of lava it creates by melting rock and sand.

Name: Roaring Moon
Pokedex Entry: It is possible that this is the creature listed as Roaring Moon in an expedition journal that still holds many mysteries.

Name: Iron Valiant
Pokedex Entry: It has some similarities to a mad scientist’s invention covered in a paranormal magazine.

Name: Koraidon
Pokedex Entry: This seems to be the Winged King mentioned in an old expedition journal. It was said to have split the land with its bare fists.

Name: Miraidon
Pokedex Entry: Much remains unknown about this creature. It resembles Cyclizar but it is far more ruthless and powerful.

Name: Walking Wake
Pokedex Entry: This ferocious creature is shrouded in mystery. It’s named after an aquatic monster mentioned in an old expedition journal.

Name: Iron Leaves
Pokedex Entry: Many of its physical characteristics match those of a Virizion from the future that was covered in a paranormal magazine.

Name: Dipplin
Pokedex Entry: Dipplin is two creatures in one Pokemon. Its evolution was triggered by a special apple grown only in one place.

Name: Poltchageist
Pokedex Entry: Supposedly the regrets of a tea ceremony master who died before perfecting his craft lingered in some matcha and became a Pokemon.

Name: Sinistcha
Pokedex Entry: It pretends to be tea trying to fool people into drinking it so it can drain their life-force. Its ruse is generally unsuccessful.

Name: Okidogi
Pokedex Entry: After all its muscles were stimulated by the toxic chain around its neck Okidogi transformed and gained a powerful physique.

Name: Munkidori
Pokedex Entry: The chain is made from toxins that enhance capabilities. It stimulated Munkidori’s brain and caused the Pokemon’s psychic powers to bloom.

Name: Fenzandipiti
Pokedex Entry: Fezandipiti owes its beautiful looks and lovely voice to the toxic stimulants emanating from the chain wrapped around its body.

Name: Ogerpon
Pokedex Entry: This Pokemon’s type changes based on which mask it’s wearing. It confounds its enemies with nimble movements and kicks.

Name: Archaludon
Pokedex Entry: It gathers static electricity from its surroundings. The beams it launches when down on all fours are tremendously powerful.

Name: Hydrapple
Pokedex Entry: Seven syrpents live inside an apple made of syrup. The syrpent in the center is the commander.

Name: Gouging Fire
Pokedex Entry: There are scant few reports of this creature being sighted. One short video shows it rampaging and spouting pillars of flame.

Name: Raging Bolt
Pokedex Entry: It’s said to incinerate everything around it with lightning launched from its fur. Very little is known about this creature.

Name: Iron Boulder
Pokedex Entry: It resembles a Pokemon described in a dubious magazine as a Terrakion that had been modified by an evil organization.

Name: Iron Crown
Pokedex Entry: It resembles a mysterious object introduced in a paranormal magazine as a cutting-edge weapon shaped like a Cobalion.

Name: Terapagos
Pokedex Entry: Terapagos protects itself using its power to transform energy into hard crystals. This Pokemon is the source of the Terastal phenomenon.

Name: Pecharunt
Pokedex Entry: It feeds others toxic mochi that draw out desires and capabilities. Those who eat the mochi fall under Pecharunt’s control chained to its will.
